¢╣µ│Ģ\n205: \n206: ```python\n207: class PackRuntime:\n208:     def __init__(self, verbose: bool = False) -> None: ...\n209:     def pack(self, workspace_path: Path, **options: Any) -> Dict[str, Any]: ...\n210:     def _validate_workspace_structure(self, workspace_path: Path) -> None: ...\n211:     def _load_or_create_metadata(self, workspace_path: Path, options: Dict[str, Any]) -> AgentMetadata: ...\n212:     def _apply_option_overrides(self, metadata: AgentMetadata, options: Dict[str, Any]) -> AgentMetadata: ...\n213:     def _validate_language_compatibility(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata: AgentMetadata) -> None: ...\n214:     def _process_dependencies(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata: AgentMetadata) -> None: ...\n215:     def _generate_dockerfile(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata: AgentMetadata) -> Optional[Path]: ...\n216:     def _update_pack_metadata(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata: AgentMetadata, dockerfile_path: Optional[Path]) -> None: ...\n217: ```\n218: \n219: ### 5.3 AgentMetadata µĢ░µŹ«µ©ĪÕ×ŗ\n220: \n221: | ÕŁŚµ«Ą | ń▒╗Õ×ŗ | ķ╗śĶ«żÕĆ╝ | µĀĪķ¬īĶ¦äÕłÖ |\n222: |------|------|---------|----------|\n223: | agent_name | str | required | - |\n224: | language | str | \"python\" | Õ┐ģķĪ╗õĖ║ python µł¢ java’╝łÕ░ÅÕåÖ’╝ē |\n225: | entrypoint | str | required | - |\n226: | port | int | 8080 | ĶīāÕø┤ 1-65535 |\n227: | build_mode | str | \"local\" | Õ┐ģķĪ╗õĖ║ local µł¢ cloud’╝łÕ░ÅÕåÖ’╝ē |\n228: | description | Optional[str] | None | - |\n229: | version | Optional[str] | None | - |\n230: | requirements_file | Optional[str] | \"requirements.txt\" | - |\n231: \n232: ### 5.4 µłÉÕŖ¤ĶŠōÕć║ńż║õŠŗ\n233: \n234: ```\n235: Pack completed successfully!\n236:   Agent name: my-agent\n237:   Workspace: /path/to/workspace\n238:   Metadata: /path/to/workspace/agent_metadata.yaml\n239: ```\n240: \n241: ---\n242: \n243: ## 6. Õ«×µ¢ĮĶ«ĪÕłÆ\n244: \n245: | ķśČµ«Ą | ÕåģÕ«╣ | ķóäõ╝░ÕĘźµŚČ |\n246: |------|------|----------|\n247: | P1 | Typer app µĪåµ×Č + pack ÕæĮõ╗żÕÅéµĢ░Õ«Üõ╣ē | 1d |\n248: | P2 | PackRuntime.pack ÕģźÕÅŻ + ÕĘźõĮ£ń®║ķŚ┤ķ¬īĶ»ü | 1d |\n249: | P3 | ÕģāµĢ░µŹ«ÕŖĀĶĮĮ/ÕłøÕ╗║/õ┐ØÕŁś + ÕÅéµĢ░Ķ”åńø¢ | 1d |\n250: | P4 | Ķ»ŁĶ©ĆÕģ╝Õ«╣µĆ¦ķ¬īĶ»ü + Dockerfile ńö¤µłÉ | 1d |\n251: | P5 | ÕŹĢÕģāµĄŗĶ»Ģ + ķöÖĶ»»ÕżäńÉå | 1d |\n252: \n253: **µĆ╗Ķ«Ī**: ~5 õ║║Õż®\n254: \n255: ---\n256: \n257: ## 7. ÕÅéĶĆāµ¢ćµĪŻ\n258: \n259: - cli-toolkit/design.md: CLI Ķ«ŠĶ«Īµ¢ćµĪŻ\n260: - cli-toolkit/spec.md: CLI Ķ¦äĶīāµ¢ćµĪŻ\n261: - Typer: https://typer.tiangolo.com/\n262: - Pydantic: https://docs.pydantic.dev/\n\n(End of file - total 262 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-020: CLI pack ÕæĮõ╗ż\n\n## µ”éĶ┐░\n\n| Õ▒×µĆ¦ | ÕĆ╝ |\n|------|-----|\n| AR | AR-020 |\n| Module | cmd/cli |\n| Language | Python |\n| Size | M |\n\n---\n\n## 1. Purpose (ńø«ńÜä)\n\nÕ«×ńÄ░ AgentCube CLI ńÜä `pack` ÕæĮõ╗ż’╝īńö©õ║Äķ¬īĶ»üÕÆīÕćåÕżć agent ÕĘźõĮ£ń®║ķŚ┤’╝īÕÉłÕ╣Č CLI ÕÅéµĢ░Ķ”åńø¢Õł░ÕģāµĢ░µŹ«µ¢ćõ╗Č’╝īÕÅ»ķĆēńö¤µłÉ Dockerfile’╝īÕ╣ČµŖźÕæŖµēōÕīģÕÉÄńÜäĶĘ»ÕŠäõ┐Īµü»ŃĆéĶ┐Öµś» agent ńö¤ÕæĮÕæ©µ£¤ń«ĪńÉåńÜäń¼¼õĖĆµŁź’╝īõĖ║ÕÉÄń╗Ł `build`ŃĆü`publish`ŃĆü`invoke` ńŁēÕæĮõ╗żÕźĀÕ«ÜÕ¤║ńĪĆŃĆé\n\n---\n\n## 2. Scope (ĶīāÕø┤)","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/proposal.md","time":{"start":1775871197449,"end":1775871197462}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775871197467,"sessionID":"ses_285d45783ffe7V0U1N5fK5jOTG","part":{"id":"prt_d7a2bfd95001D43tXjySTxuFj3","messageID":"msg_d7a2be15f0016vXhsdZ1XFAzUg","sessionID":"ses_285d45783ffe7V0U1N5fK5jOTG","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-6169dee57bc448a8bb65954f6cbcdde7","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/delta-spec.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/delta-spec.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Delta Specification ŌĆö CLI pack Command\n2: \n3: AR: AR-020 ŌĆö CLI pack ÕæĮõ╗ż\n4: Module: cmd/cli\n5: Language: Python\n6: Size: M\n7: \n8: ---\n9: \n10: ## Requirement: Pack Command Entry Point\n11: \n12: The system SHALL provide a `pack` subcommand via Typer application to validate and prepare a workspace, merge CLI overrides into metadata, optionally generate a Dockerfile, and report paths.\n13: \n14: ### Scenario: Options and Defaults\n15: \n16: - **GIVEN** the user runs `pack` without specifying any options\n17: - **WHEN** the command is invoked\n18: - **THEN** the CLI SHALL use the following defaults:\n19:   - `workspace` = \".\" (`-f` / `--workspace`, type `str`)\n20:   - `agent_name` = `None` (`--agent-name`, type `Optional[str]`)\n21:   - `language` = `None` (`--language`, type `Optional[str]`)\n22:   - `entrypoint` = `None` (`--entrypoint`, type `Optional[str]`)\n23:   - `port` = `None` (`--port`, type `Optional[int]`)\n24:   - `build_mode` = `None` (`--build-mode`, type `Optional[str]`)\n25:   - `description` = `None` (`--description`, type `Optional[str]`)\n26:   - `output` = `None` (`--output`, type `Optional[str]`)\n27:   - `verbose` = `False` (`--verbose`, type `bool`)\n28: \n29: ### Scenario: Successful Pack\n30: \n31: - **GIVEN** a valid workspace path with required files for the specified language\n32: - **WHEN** `pack` completes without exception\n33: - **THEN** the CLI SHALL:\n34:   - Display a Rich Progress spinner during execution\n35:   - Print success message including `agent_name`, resolved `workspace_path`, and `metadata_path`\n36:   - Report `metadata_path` as `{final_workspace}/agent_metadata.yaml`\n37: \n38: ### Scenario: Pack Failure Handling with Verbose\n39: \n40: - **GIVEN** `PackRuntime.pack` raises an exception\n41: - **WHEN** `verbose` is `True`\n42: - **THEN** the CLI SHALL:\n43:   - Print `Error packaging agent: {e}` in red\n44:   - Print the full traceback\n45:   - Exit with code `1`\n46: \n47: ### Scenario: Pack Failure Handling without Verbose\n48: \n49: - **GIVEN** `PackRuntime.pack` raises an exception\n50: - **WHEN** `verbose` is `False`\n51: - **THEN** the CLI SHALL:\n52:   - Print `Error packaging agent: {e}` in red\n53:   - Exit with code `1` without printing traceback\n54: \n55: ---\n56: \n57: ## Requirement: Workspace Validation\n58: \n59: The system SHALL validate that the workspace path exists, is a directory, and contains language-specific required files.\n60: \n61: ### Scenario: Missing Workspace Directory\n62: \n63: - **GIVEN** the `workspace_path` does not exist on the filesystem\n64: - **WHEN** `PackRuntime._validate_workspace_structure` runs\n65: - **THEN** the system SHALL raise `ValueError` with a message indicating the directory does not exist\n66: \n67: ### Scenario: Workspace is Not a Directory\n68: \n69: - **GIVEN** the `workspace_path` exists but is not a directory\n70: - **WHEN** `PackRuntime._validate_workspace_structure` runs\n71: - **THEN** the system SHALL raise `ValueError` with a message indicating the path is not a directory\n72: \n73: ### Scenario: Python Workspace Without Python Files\n74: \n75: - **GIVEN** `metadata.language == \"python\"` and the workspace is a valid directory\n76: - **WHEN** no `*.py` files exist in the workspace root\n77: - **THEN** the system SHALL raise `ValueError(\"No Python files found in workspace\")`\n78: \n79: ### Scenario: Java Workspace Without pom.xml\n80: \n81: - **GIVEN** `metadata.language == \"java\"` and the workspace is a valid directory\n82: - **WHEN** no `pom.xml` file exists in the workspace\n83: - **THEN** the system SHALL raise `ValueError` indicating `pom.xml` is required for Java projects\n84: \n85: ---\n86: \n87: ## Requirement: Metadata Loading and Creation\n88: \n89: The system SHALL load existing metadata from YAML or create new metadata with defaults when the file does not exist.\n90: \n91: ### Scenario: Load Existing Metadata from Primary File\n92: \n93: - **GIVEN** `{workspace}/agent_metadata.yaml` exists\n94: - **WHEN** `PackRuntime._load_or_create_metadata` runs\n95: - **THEN** the system SHALL load metadata from `agent_metadata.yaml` and parse as `AgentMetadata`\n96: \n97: ### Scenario: Load Existing Metadata from Fallback Files\n98: \n99: - **GIVEN** `agent_metadata.yaml` does not exist but `agent.yaml` exists\n100: - **WHEN** `PackRuntime._load_or_create_metadata` runs\n101: - **THEN** the system SHALL load metadata from `agent.yaml`\n102: \n103: ### Scenario: Load Existing Metadata from Secondary Fallback\n104: \n105: - **GIVEN** neither `agent_metadata.yaml` nor `agent.yaml` exists but `metadata.yaml` exists\n106: - **WHEN** `PackRuntime._load_or_create_metadata` runs\n107: - **THEN** the system SHALL load metadata from `metadata.yaml`\n108: \n109: ### Scenario: Create New Metadata When No File Exists\n110: \n111: - **GIVEN** none of `agent_metadata.yaml`, `agent.yaml`, or `metadata.yaml` exist\n112: - **WHEN** `PackRuntime._load_or_create_metadata` runs\n113: - **THEN** the system SHALL:\n114:   - Create a new `AgentMetadata` with default values\n115:   - Set `agent_name` from CLI option or infer from workspace directory name\n116:   - Set `language` from CLI option or default to \"python\"\n117:   - Set `port` from CLI option or default to `8080`\n118:   - Set `build_mode` from CLI option or default to \"local\"\n119: \n120: ---\n121: \n122: ## Requirement: Option Overrides\n123: \n124: The system SHALL merge CLI option overrides into loaded or created metadata.\n125: \n126: ### Scenario: Override Agent Name\n127: \n128: - **GIVEN** metadata exists with `agent_name = \"original-name\"`\n129: - **WHEN** CLI option `--agent-name \"new-name\"` is provided\n130: - **THEN** `PackRuntime._apply_option_overrides` SHALL update `agent_name` to \"new-name\"\n131: \n132: ### Scenario: Override Language\n133: \n134: - **GIVEN** metadata exists with `language = \"python\"`\n135: - **WHEN** CLI option `--language java` is provided\n136: - **THEN** the system SHALL update `language` to \"java\" and validate Java workspace compatibility\n137: \n138: ### Scenario: Override Entrypoint\n139: \n140: - **GIVEN** metadata exists with `entrypoint = \"python main.py\"`\n141: - **WHEN** CLI option `--entrypoint \"python app.py\"` is provided\n142: - **THEN** the system SHALL update `entrypoint` to \"python app.py\"\n143: \n144: ### Scenario: Override Port\n145: \n146: - **GIVEN** metadata exists with `port = 8080`\n147: - **WHEN** CLI option `--port 9000` is provided\n148: - **THEN** the system SHALL update `port` to `9000` and validate the port range `1..65535`\n149: \n150: ### Scenario: Override Build Mode\n151: \n152: - **GIVEN** metadata exists with `build_mode = \"local\"`\n153: - **WHEN** CLI option `--build-mode cloud` is provided\n154: - **THEN** the system SHALL update `build_mode` to \"cloud\"\n155: \n156: ### Scenario: Override Description\n157: \n158: - **GIVEN** metadata exists with `description = None`\n159: - **WHEN** CLI option `--description \"My AI agent\"` is provided\n160: - **THEN** the system SHALL update `description` to \"My AI agent\"\n161: \n162: ---\n163: \n164: ## Requirement: Language Compatibility Validation\n165: \n166: The system SHALL validate workspace compatibility with the specified or inferred language.\n167: \n168: ### Scenario: Validate Python Workspace Structure\n169: \n170: - **GIVEN** `metadata.language == \"python\"`\n171: - **WHEN** `PackRuntime._validate_python_compatibility` runs\n172: - **THEN** the system SHALL:\n173:   - Check for presence of at least one `*.py` file\n174:   - Optionally check for `requirements.txt` or `pyproject.toml`\n175:   - Raise `ValueError` if Python files are missing\n176: \n177: ### Scenario: Validate Java Workspace Structure\n178: \n179: - **GIVEN** `metadata.language == \"java\"`\n180: - **WHEN** `PackRuntime._validate_java_compatibility` runs\n181: - **THEN** the system SHALL:\n182:   - Check for presence of `pom.xml`\n183:   - Raise `ValueError` if `pom.xml` is missing\n184: \n185: ### Scenario: Invalid Language Value\n186: \n187: - **GIVEN** CLI option `--language ruby` is provided\n188: - **WHEN** metadata is validated\n189: - **THEN** Pydantic SHALL raise validation error because `language` must be `python` or `java` (lowercase)\n190: \n191: ---\n192: \n193: ## Requirement: Entrypoint Inference\n194: \n195: The system SHALL infer the entrypoint command based on language and workspace contents when not explicitly provided.\n196: \n197: ### Scenario: Infer Python Entrypoint from main.py\n198: \n199: - **GIVEN** `language = \"python\"` and `entrypoint` is not provided\n200: - **WHEN** `main.py` exists in the workspace\n201: - **THEN** `PackRuntime._infer_entrypoint` SHALL return `\"python main.py\"`\n202: \n203: ### Scenario: Infer Python Entrypoint from app.py\n204: \n205: - **GIVEN** `language = \"python\"` and `entrypoint` is not provided and `main.py` does not exist\n206: - **WHEN** `app.py` exists in the workspace\n207: - **THEN** the system SHALL infer `\"python app.py\"`\n208: \n209: ### Scenario: Infer Python Entrypoint from First py File\n210: \n211: - **GIVEN** `language = \"python\"` and neither `main.py` nor `app.py` exist\n212: - **WHEN** other `*.py` files exist (e.g., `agent.py`)\n213: - **THEN** the system SHALL infer `\"python {first_py_file}\"`\n214: \n215: ### Scenario: Infer Java Entrypoint\n216: \n217: - **GIVEN** `language = \"java\"` and `entrypoint` is not provided\n218: - **WHEN** `pom.xml` exists\n219: - **THEN** the system SHALL infer a Maven-based entrypoint (e.g., `\"java -jar target/*.jar\"` or appropriate command)\n220: \n221: ---\n222: \n223: ## Requirement: Dependency Processing\n224: \n225: The system SHALL process language-specific dependencies and prepare them for containerization.\n226: \n227: ### Scenario: Process Python Dependencies from requirements.txt\n228: \n229: - **GIVEN** `language = \"python\"` and `requirements.txt` exists\n230: - **WHEN** `PackRuntime._process_python_dependencies` runs\n231: - **THEN** the system SHALL:\n232:   - Copy `requirements.txt` to the packaging context\n233:   - Record `requirements_file` in metadata as `\"requirements.txt\"`\n234: \n235: ### Scenario: Process Python Dependencies from pyproject.toml\n236: \n237: - **GIVEN** `language = \"python\"` and `pyproject.toml` exists (no `requirements.txt`)\n238: - **WHEN** dependency processing runs\n239: - **THEN** the system SHALL handle `pyproject.toml` based dependencies\n240: \n241: ### Scenario: Process Java Dependencies from pom.xml\n242: \n243: - **GIVEN** `language = \"java\"` and `pom.xml` exists\n244: - **WHEN** `PackRuntime._process_java_dependencies` runs\n245: - **THEN** the system SHALL copy `pom.xml` and prepare Maven build context\n246: \n247: ---\n248: \n249: ## Requirement: Dockerfile Generation\n250: \n251: The system SHALL generate a language-appropriate Dockerfile when one does not exist in the workspace.\n252: \n253: ### Scenario: Generate Python Dockerfile\n254: \n255: - **GIVEN** `language = \"python\"` and no existing Dockerfile\n256: - **WHEN** `PackRuntime._generate_python_dockerfile` runs\n257: - **THEN** the generated Dockerfile SHALL:\n258:   - Use a Python base image (e.g., `python:3.10-slim`)\n259:   - Install dependencies from `requirements.txt` if present\n260:   - Copy source files\n261:   - Set the entrypoint from metadata\n262:   - Expose the port from metadata\n263: \n264: ### Scenario: Generate Java Dockerfile\n265: \n266: - **GIVEN** `language = \"java\"` and no existing Dockerfile\n267: - **WHEN** `PackRuntime._generate_java_dockerfile` runs\n268: - **THEN** the generated Dockerfile SHALL:\n269:   - Use a Maven/Java base image (multi-stage build)\n270:   - Build from `pom.xml`\n271:   - Copy the built JAR\n272:   - Set the entrypoint from metadata\n273:   - Expose the port from metadata\n274: \n275: ### Scenario: Skip Dockerfile Generation if Exists\n276: \n277: - **GIVEN** a `Dockerfile` already exists in the workspace\n278: - **WHEN** `PackRuntime._generate_dockerfile` runs\n279: - **THEN** the system SHALL:\n280:   - Not overwrite the existing Dockerfile\n281:   - Return `None` or the path to the existing Dockerfile\n282:   - Log that existing Dockerfile will be used\n283: \n284: ### Scenario: Dockerfile Path Update in Metadata\n285: \n286: - **GIVEN** a Dockerfile is generated or exists\n287: - **WHEN** `PackRuntime._update_pack_metadata` runs\n288: - **THEN** the metadata SHALL be updated with Dockerfile path reference\n289: \n290: ---\n291: \n292: ## Requirement: Output Path Preparation\n293: \n294: The system SHALL prepare the output path for packaging when specified.\n295: \n296: ### Scenario: Use Specified Output Path\n297: \n298: - **GIVEN** CLI option `--output /path/to/output.tar.gz` is provided\n299: - **WHEN** `PackRuntime._prepare_output_path` runs\n300: - **THEN** the system SHALL:\n301:   - Validate the parent directory exists\n302:   - Return the absolute path for the output archive\n303: \n304: ### Scenario: Default Output Path\n305: \n306: - **GIVEN** `--output` is not specified\n307: - **WHEN** output path is prepared\n308: - **THEN** the system SHALL use a default output location based on workspace (e.g., `{workspace}/{agent_name}-packaged.tar.gz`)\n309: \n310: ### Scenario: Create Output Parent Directory\n311: \n312: - **GIVEN** output path parent directory does not exist\n313: - **WHEN** output path is prepared\n314: - **THEN** the system SHALL create the parent directory\n315: \n316: ---\n317: \n318: ## Requirement: Metadata Schema Validation\n319: \n320: The system SHALL validate metadata against the `AgentMetadata` Pydantic model.\n321: \n322: ### Scenario: Valid Metadata Fields\n323: \n324: - **GIVEN** metadata YAML is loaded\n325: - **WHEN** `AgentMetadata` model validation runs\n326: - **THEN** all fields SHALL conform to their types and constraints:\n327:   - `agent_name` is required `str`\n328:   - `language` is `str` with validator allowing only `python` or `java` (lowercase)\n329:   - `port` is `int` in range `1..65535`\n330:   - `build_mode` is `str` with validator allowing only `local` or `cloud` (lowercase)\n331: \n332: ### Scenario: Invalid Language Rejected\n333: \n334: - **GIVEN** metadata contains `language = \"ruby\"`\n335: - **WHEN** Pydantic validation runs\n336: - **THEN** the validator SHALL raise `ValidationError` indicating language must be `python` or `java`\n337: \n338: ### Scenario: Invalid Port Range Rejected\n339: \n340: - **GIVEN** metadata contains `port = 70000`\n341: - **WHEN** Pydantic validation runs\n342: - **THEN** the validator SHALL raise `ValidationError` indicating port must be in range `1..65535`\n343: \n344: ### Scenario: Invalid Build Mode Rejected\n345: \n346: - **GIVEN** metadata contains `build_mode = \"docker\"`\n347: - **WHEN** Pydantic validation runs\n348: - **THEN** the validator SHALL raise `ValidationError` indicating build_mode must be `local` or `cloud`\n349: \n350: ---\n351: \n352: ## Requirement: Metadata Save Location\n353: \n354: The system SHALL persist metadata as YAML in a canonical location.\n355: \n356: ### Scenario: Save Metadata to Canonical Path\n357: \n358: - **GIVEN** metadata is updated during pack\n359: - **WHEN** `MetadataService.save_metadata` runs\n360: - **THEN** the file SHALL be written to `{workspace}/agent_metadata.yaml` using:\n361:   - `yaml.dump` with `default_flow_style=False`\n362:   - `indent=2`\n363:   - `sort_keys=False`\n364:   - `model_dump(exclude_none=True)` to exclude None fields\n365: \n366: ---\n367: \n368: ## Requirement: Pack Result Structure\n369: \n370: The system SHALL return a structured result from `PackRuntime.pack`.\n371: \n372: ### Scenario: Return Pack Result Dictionary\n373: \n374: - **GIVEN** `PackRuntime.pack` completes successfully\n375: - **WHEN** the method returns\n376: - **THEN** the result SHALL be a `Dict[str, Any]` containing:\n377:   - `agent_name`: the resolved agent name\n378:   - `workspace_path`: absolute path to the workspace\n379:   - `metadata_path`: path to the saved metadata file\n380:   - `dockerfile_path`: path to generated or existing Dockerfile (or `None`)\n381:   - `language`: the resolved language\n382:   - `entrypoint`: the resolved entrypoint command\n383:   - `port`: the resolved port number\n384: \n385: ---\n386: \n387: ## Requirement: Global Verbose Logging on Pack\n388: \n389: The system SHALL enable verbose logging when `--verbose` is passed to the pack command.\n390: \n391: ### Scenario: Verbose Logging Enabled\n392: \n393: - **GIVEN** the user passes `--verbose` to the pack command\n394: - **WHEN** the pack command runs\n395: - **THEN** `PackRuntime` SHALL:\n396:   - Set `verbose=True` in the runtime constructor\n397:   - Log detailed progress messages during each step\n398:   - Include file paths and intermediate results in logs\n399: \n400: ---\n401: \n402: ## Requirement: PackRuntime Initialization\n403: \n404: The system SHALL construct `PackRuntime` with appropriate configuration.\n405: \n406: ### Scenario: PackRuntime Constructor\n407: \n408: - **GIVEN** `PackRuntime(verbose=False)` is constructed\n409: - **WHEN** the instance is created\n410: - **THEN** the runtime SHALL:\n411:   - Initialize `MetadataService` for metadata operations\n412:   - Initialize `DockerService` if Docker integration is needed\n413:   - Store the `verbose` flag for logging control\n414: \n415: ---\n416: \n417: ## Requirement: MetadataOptions Conversion\n418: \n419: The system SHALL convert CLI options to `MetadataOptions` dataclass.\n420: \n421: ### Scenario: Convert Options to MetadataOptions\n422: \n423: - **GIVEN** CLI options dict with keys matching `MetadataOptions` fields\n424: - **WHEN** `MetadataOptions.from_options(options)` runs\n425: - **THEN** the system SHALL create a `MetadataOptions` instance with:\n426:   - All optional fields populated from corresponding option values\n427:   - Defaults applied for missing optional fields per dataclass definition\n428: \n429: ---\n430: \n431: ## Requirement: Pack Command Error Display\n432: \n433: The system SHALL display errors appropriately based on verbose mode.\n434: \n435: ### Scenario: Display Error with Traceback in Verbose Mode\n436: \n437: - **GIVEN** an exception occurs during pack and `verbose=True`\n438: - **WHEN** `_handle_error` is called\n439: - **THEN** the CLI SHALL:\n440:   - Print `Error packaging agent: {exception_message}` in red via Rich\n441:   - Print the full Python traceback\n442:   - Call `typer.Exit(1)` to terminate\n443: \n444: ### Scenario: Display Error Without Traceback in Non-Verbose Mode\n445: \n446: - **GIVEN** an exception occurs during pack and `verbose=False`\n447: - **WHEN** `_handle_error` is called\n448: - **THEN** the CLI SHALL:\n449:   - Print `Error packaging agent: {exception_message}` in red via Rich\n450:   - NOT print traceback\n451:   - Call `typer.Exit(1)` to terminate\n452: \n453: ---\n454: \n455: ## Requirement: Workspace Path Resolution\n456: \n457: The system SHALL resolve the workspace path to an absolute path.\n458: \n459: ### Scenario: Resolve Relative Workspace Path\n460: \n461: - **GIVEN** `workspace = \".\"` (relative path)\n462: - **WHEN** the pack command processes the workspace\n463: - **THEN** the system SHALL resolve it to an absolute path using `Path(workspace).resolve()`\n464: \n465: ### Scenario: Resolve Absolute Workspace Path\n466: \n467: - **GIVEN** `workspace = \"/home/user/my-agent\"` (absolute path)\n468: - **WHEN** the pack command processes the workspace\n469: - **THEN** the system SHALL use the path as-is or normalize it\n470: \n471: ---\n472: \n473: ## Requirement: Progress Indicator During Pack\n474: \n475: The system SHALL display a progress spinner during pack operations.\n476: \n477: ### Scenario: Rich Progress Spinner Display\n478: \n479: - **GIVEN** the pack command is executing\n480: - **WHEN** operations like metadata loading, validation, and Dockerfile generation run\n481: - **THEN** the CLI SHALL display a Rich Progress spinner with descriptive text (e.g., \"Packaging agent...\")\n482: \n483: ---\n484: \n485: ## Requirement: Multi-File Workspace Handling\n486: \n487: The system SHALL handle workspaces with multiple source files appropriately.\n488: \n489: ### Scenario: Python Workspace with Multiple Files\n490: \n491: - **GIVEN** a Python workspace with `main.py`, `utils.py`, `config.py`, and `requirements.txt`\n492: - **WHEN** pack runs\n493: - **THEN** the system SHALL:\n494:   - Identify all `.py` files for validation\n495:   - Copy all source files to the packaging context\n496:   - Include `requirements.txt` in dependency processing\n497: \n498: ---\n499: \n500: ## Requirement: Pack Command Help Text\n501: \n502: The system SHALL provide help text for all pack command options.\n503: \n504: ### Scenario: Pack Command Help Display\n505: \n506: - **GIVEN** the user runs `pack --help`\n507: - **WHEN** the help is displayed\n508: - **THEN** Typer SHALL show:\n509:   - Command description\n510:   - All options with their names, types, defaults, and help strings\n511:   - Usage examples if configured\n512: \n513: ---\n514: \n515: ## Implementation Files\n516: \n517: | File | Purpose |\n518: |------|---------|\n519: | `agentcube/cli/main.py` | Typer `pack` command definition |\n520: | `agentcube/runtime/pack_runtime.py` | `PackRuntime` implementation |\n521: | `agentcube/services/metadata_service.py` | `MetadataService` for metadata operations |\n522: | `agentcube/models/pack_models.py` | `MetadataOptions` dataclass |\n523: \n524: ---\n525: \n526: ## Dependencies\n527: \n528: | Package | Purpose |\n529: |---------|---------|\n530: | `typer[all]>=0.9.0` | CLI framework with Rich integration |\n531: | `pydantic>=2.0.0` | Metadata model validation |\n532: | `pyyaml>=6.0` | YAML metadata file handling |\n533: | `rich>=13.0.0` | Progress spinner and error display |\n534: | `pathlib` | Path resolution and validation |\n535: \n536: ---\n537: \n538: ## Validation Checklist\n539: \n540: - [ ] Pack command registered in Typer app with correct options\n541: - [ ] Options have correct types and defaults matching spec\n542: - [ ] Workspace validation checks existence and directory type\n543: - [ ] Language-specific file validation for Python and Java\n544: - [ ] Metadata loaded from `agent_metadata.yaml` with fallbacks\n545: - [ ] New metadata created with defaults when file missing\n546: - [ ] CLI option overrides applied to metadata\n547: - [ ] Entrypoint inferred based on language and files\n548: - [ ] Dockerfile generated with language-specific template\n549: - [ ] Existing Dockerfile not overwritten\n550: - [ ] Metadata saved to canonical path with correct YAML format\n551: - [ ] Pack result returns structured dictionary\n552: - [ ] Verbose mode enables detailed logging\n553: - [ ] Error handling prints traceback in verbose mode\n554: - [ ] Rich Progress spinner displayed during execution\n555: - [ ] Pydantic validation rejects invalid language/port/build_mode\n\n(End of file - total 555 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# Delta Specification ŌĆö CLI pack Command\n\nAR: AR-020 ŌĆö CLI pack ÕæĮõ╗ż\nModule: cmd/cli\nLanguage: Python\nSize: M\n\n---\n\n## Requirement: Pack Command Entry Point\n\nThe system SHALL provide a `pack` subcommand via Typer application to validate and prepare a workspace, merge CLI overrides into metadata, optionally generate a Dockerfile, and report paths.\n\n### Scenario: Options and Defaults\n\n- **GIVEN** the user runs `pack` without specifying any options\n- **WHEN** the command is invoked\n- **THEN** the CLI SHALL use the following defaults:\n  - `workspace` = \".\" (`-f` / `--workspace`, type `str`)\n  - `agent_name` = `None` (`--agent-name`, type `Optional[str]`)","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/delta-spec.md","time":{"start":1775871197452,"end":1775871197465}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775871197471,"sessionID":"ses_285d45783ffe7V0U1N5fK5jOTG","part":{"id":"prt_d7a2c00c6001B76AOPS4Miqw7S","messageID":"msg_d7a2be15f0016vXhsdZ1XFAzUg","sessionID":"ses_285d45783ffe7V0U1N5fK5jOTG","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-34109e6fb8194027a331b6e34e462d4c","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-017/delta-spec.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-017/delta-spec.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Delta Spec: AR-017 ŌĆö PicoD JWT õĖŁķŚ┤õ╗Č\n2: \n3: **Module:** `pkg/picod`  \n4: **Language:** Go  \n5: **Size:** S\n6: \n7: ---\n8: \n9: ## Overview\n10: \n11: Implement a dedicated JWT authentication middleware for PicoD that provides secure RS256 token validation, runtime public key management for key rotation, and request body size limiting. This middleware ensures that all PicoD API endpoints (except health check) require valid JWT tokens issued by the Router, protecting sandbox pods from unauthorized access.\n12: \n13: ---\n14: \n15: ## GIVEN/WHEN/THEN Scenarios\n16: \n17: ### Requirement: AuthManager type definition\n18: \n19: The system SHALL define `AuthManager` for RSA JWT authentication with thread-safe public key storage.\n20: \n21: #### Scenario: AuthManager struct definition\n22: - **GIVEN** `pkg/picod/auth.go`\n23: - **WHEN** reading the `AuthManager` struct\n24: - **THEN** the struct SHALL contain fields:\n25:   - `publicKey *rsa.PublicKey` for RSA public key\n26:   - `mutex sync.RWMutex` for thread-safe public key access\n27: \n28: #### Scenario: AuthManager thread-safe storage\n29: - **GIVEN** `pkg/picod/auth.go`\n30: - **WHEN** accessing publicKey concurrently\n31: - **THEN** read operations SHALL use `mutex.RLock()` / `mutex.RUnlock()`\n32: - AND write operations SHALL use `mutex.Lock()` / `mutex.Unlock()`\n33: \n34: ---\n35: \n36: ### Requirement: Public key environment variable\n37: \n38: The system SHALL define constant for public key environment variable name.\n39: \n40: #### Scenario: PublicKeyEnvVar constant\n41: - **GIVEN** `pkg/picod/auth.go`\n42: - **WHEN** reading constants\n43: - **THEN** `PublicKeyEnvVar` SHALL be `\"PICOD_AUTH_PUBLIC_KEY\"`\n44: \n45: #### Scenario: MaxBodySize constant\n46: - **GIVEN** `pkg/picod/auth.go`\n47: - **WHEN** reading constants\n48: - **THEN** `MaxBodySize` SHALL be `32 << 20` (32 MiB)\n49: \n50: ---\n51: \n52: ### Requirement: NewAuthManager constructor\n53: \n54: The system SHALL implement `NewAuthManager` constructor for AuthManager initialization.\n55: \n56: #### Scenario: NewAuthManager initialization\n57: - **GIVEN** `pkg/picod/auth.go`\n58: - **WHEN** calling `NewAuthManager()`\n59: - **THEN** `LoadPublicKeyFromEnv()` SHALL be called\n60: - AND `publicKey` SHALL be set from PEM public key\n61: - AND `AuthManager` SHALL be returned with initialized publicKey\n62: - AND error SHALL be returned if env var is missing\n63: - AND error SHALL be returned if PEM decode fails\n64: - AND error SHALL be returned if PKIX parse fails\n65: \n66: #### Scenario: NewAuthManager startup fatal handling\n67: - **GIVEN** `pkg/picod/server.go`\n68: - **WHEN** `NewAuthManager()` returns error\n69: - **THEN** `NewServer` SHALL return error with wrapped message\n70: - AND caller (`cmd/picod/main.go`) SHALL call `klog.Fatalf` on failure\n71: \n72: ---\n73: \n74: ### Requirement: LoadPublicKeyFromEnv function\n75: \n76: The system SHALL implement public key loading from environment variable with PKIX format validation.\n77: \n78: #### Scenario: LoadPublicKeyFromEnv environment read\n79: - **GIVEN** `pkg/picod/auth.go`\n80: - **WHEN** loading public key\n81: - **THEN** `os.Getenv(PublicKeyEnvVar)` SHALL be called\n82: - AND `strings.TrimSpace()` SHALL remove leading/trailing whitespace\n83: - AND error SHALL be returned if env var is empty\n84: \n85: #### Scenario: LoadPublicKeyFromEnv PEM decode\n86: - **GIVEN** `pkg/picod/auth.go`\n87: - **WHEN** decoding PEM block\n88: - **THEN** `pem.Decode([]byte(pemKey))` SHALL be called\n89: - AND error SHALL be returned if block is nil (invalid PEM)\n90: \n91: #### Scenario: LoadPublicKeyFromEnv PEM block type validation\n92: - **GIVEN** `pkg/picod/auth.go`\n93: - **WHEN** validating PEM block type\n94: - **THEN** `block.Type` SHALL be `\"PUBLIC KEY\"` (PKIX format)\n95: - AND error SHALL be returned if block type is not `\"PUBLIC KEY\"`\n96: - AND PKCS#1 format (`\"RSA PUBLIC KEY\"` block type) SHALL be rejected\n97: \n98: #### Scenario: LoadPublicKeyFromEnv PKIX parsing\n99: - **GIVEN** `pkg/picod/auth.go`\n100: - **WHEN** parsing public key bytes\n101: - **THEN** `x509.ParsePKIXPublicKey(block.Bytes)` SHALL be called\n102: - AND error SHALL be returned if PKIX parse fails\n103: - AND result SHALL be type-asserted to `*rsa.PublicKey`\n104: \n105: #### Scenario: LoadPublicKeyFromEnv RSA validation\n106: - **GIVEN** `pkg/picod/auth.go`\n107: - **WHEN** validating key type\n108: - **THEN** type assertion `pub.(*rsa.PublicKey)` SHALL be performed\n109: - AND error SHALL be returned if key is not RSA\n110: - AND non-RSA public keys (ECDSA, DSA, Ed25519) SHALL be rejected\n111: \n112: ---\n113: \n114: ### Requirement: AuthMiddleware Bearer token extraction\n115: \n116: The system SHALL implement JWT authentication middleware with Bearer token extraction.\n117: \n118: #### Scenario: AuthMiddleware Authorization header extraction\n119: - **GIVEN** `pkg/picod/auth.go`\n120: - **WHEN** processing request with `Authorization` header\n121: - **THEN** header SHALL be extracted via `c.GetHeader(\"Authorization\")`\n122: \n123: #### Scenario: AuthMiddleware missing Authorization header\n124: - **GIVEN** request without `Authorization` header\n125: - **WHEN** AuthMiddleware processes request\n126: - **THEN** HTTP `401` SHALL be returned\n127: - AND body SHALL be `{\"error\": \"missing authorization header\"}`\n128: - AND `c.Abort()` SHALL be called\n129: \n130: #### Scenario: AuthMiddleware Bearer prefix validation\n131: - **GIVEN** request with `Authorization` header\n132: - **WHEN** AuthMiddleware validates format\n133: - **THEN** `strings.HasPrefix(authHeader, \"Bearer \")` SHALL be checked\n134: - AND HTTP `401` SHALL be returned if prefix missing\n135: - AND body SHALL be `{\"error\": \"invalid token format\"}`\n136: - AND `c.Abort()` SHALL be called\n137: \n138: #### Scenario: AuthMiddleware token string extraction\n139: - **GIVEN** valid `Authorization` header format\n140: - **WHEN** AuthMiddleware extracts token\n141: - **THEN** `strings.TrimPrefix(authHeader, \"Bearer \")` SHALL strip prefix\n142: - AND result SHALL be token string for JWT parsing\n143: \n144: ---\n145: \n146: ### Requirement: AuthMiddleware RSA signing method validation\n147: \n148: The system SHALL validate JWT signing method is RSA to prevent algorithm substitution attacks.\n149: \n150: #### Scenario: AuthMiddleware public key read lock\n151: - **GIVEN** `pkg/picod/auth.go`\n152: - **WHEN** accessing publicKey for validation\n153: - **THEN** `a.mutex.RLock()` SHALL acquire read lock\n154: - AND `pubKey := a.publicKey` SHALL read current key\n155: - AND `a.mutex.RUnlock()` SHALL release lock before parsing\n156: \n157: #### Scenario: AuthMiddleware RSA method type assertion\n158: - **GIVEN** `pkg/picod/auth.go`\n159: - **WHEN** JWT keyFunc validates signing method\n160: - **THEN** `token.Method` SHALL be type-asserted to `*jwt.SigningMethodRSA`\n161: - AND assertion success SHALL return `pubKey` for validation\n162: - AND assertion failure SHALL return error `\"invalid signing method\"`\n163: \n164: #### Scenario: AuthMiddleware HS256 attack prevention\n165: - **GIVEN** JWT token signed with HS256 (symmetric) algorithm\n166: - **WHEN** AuthMiddleware parses token\n167: - **THEN** signing method SHALL be detected as non-RSA\n168: - AND HTTP `401` SHALL be returned\n169: - AND body SHALL be `{\"error\": \"invalid signing method\"}`\n170: - AND `c.Abort()` SHALL be called\n171: \n172: #### Scenario: AuthMiddleware RSA algorithms acceptance\n173: - **GIVEN** JWT token signed with RS256, RS384, or RS512\n174: - **WHEN** AuthMiddleware parses token\n175: - **THEN** signing method SHALL be accepted as RSA\n176: - AND token SHALL be validated with public key\n177: \n178: ---\n179: \n180: ### Requirement: AuthMiddleware JWT claim validation\n181: \n182: The system SHALL validate JWT claims with expiration, issued-at, and leeway options.\n183: \n184: #### Scenario: AuthMiddleware expiration required\n185: - **GIVEN** `pkg/picod/auth.go`\n186: - **WHEN** parsing JWT\n187: - **THEN** `jwt.WithExpirationRequired()` SHALL be applied\n188: - AND tokens without `exp` claim SHALL be rejected\n189: \n190: #### Scenario: AuthMiddleware issued-at required\n191: - **GIVEN** `pkg/picod/auth.go`\n192: - **WHEN** parsing JWT\n193: - **THEN** `jwt.WithIssuedAt()` SHALL be applied\n194: - AND tokens without `iat` claim SHALL be rejected\n195: \n196: #### Scenario: AuthMiddleware leeway tolerance\n197: - **GIVEN** `pkg/picod/auth.go`\n198: - **WHEN** parsing JWT\n199: - **THEN** `jwt.WithLeeway(time.Minute)` SHALL be applied\n200: - AND clock skew up to 1 minute SHALL be tolerated\n201: \n202: #### Scenario: AuthMiddleware expired token handling\n203: - **GIVEN** JWT token with expired `exp` claim\n204: - **WHEN** AuthMiddleware validates token\n205: - **THEN** `jwt.ErrTokenExpired` SHALL be detected via `errors.Is`\n206: - AND HTTP `401` SHALL be returned\n207: - AND body SHALL be `{\"error\": \"token is expired\"}`\n208: - AND `c.Abort()` SHALL be called\n209: \n210: #### Scenario: AuthMiddleware invalid signature handling\n211: - **GIVEN** JWT token with invalid signature\n212: - **WHEN** AuthMiddleware validates token\n213: - **THEN** `jwt.ErrTokenSignatureInvalid` SHALL be detected via `errors.Is`\n214: - AND HTTP `401` SHALL be returned\n215: - AND body SHALL be `{\"error\": \"invalid signature\"}`\n216: - AND `c.Abort()` SHALL be called\n217: \n218: #### Scenario: AuthMiddleware generic error handling\n219: - **GIVEN** JWT validation failure with unrecognized error\n220: - **WHEN** AuthMiddleware validates token\n221: - **THEN** HTTP `401` SHALL be returned\n222: - AND body SHALL be `{\"error\": err.Error()}` (original error message)\n223: - AND `c.Abort()` SHALL be called\n224: \n225: ---\n226: \n227: ### Requirement: AuthMiddleware request body size limiting\n228: \n229: The system SHALL apply request body size limit after successful JWT validation.\n230: \n231: #### Scenario: AuthMiddleware MaxBytesReader application\n232: - **GIVEN** valid JWT token\n233: - **WHEN** AuthMiddleware completes validation\n234: - **THEN** `http.MaxBytesReader(c.Writer, c.Request.Body, MaxBodySize)` SHALL be applied\n235: - AND `MaxBodySize` SHALL be `32 << 20` (32 MiB)\n236: - AND request body exceeding limit SHALL be rejected\n237: \n238: #### Scenario: AuthMiddleware proceed to handler\n239: - **GIVEN** valid JWT token and successful validation\n240: - **WHEN** AuthMiddleware completes\n241: - **THEN** `c.Next()` SHALL be called\n242: - AND request SHALL proceed to handler\n243: \n244: ---\n245: \n246: ### Requirement: Key rotation support\n247: \n248: The system SHALL provide runtime public key rotation support via SetPublicKey and GetPublicKey methods.\n249: \n250: #### Scenario: SetPublicKey thread-safe update\n251: - **GIVEN** `pkg/picod/auth.go`\n252: - **WHEN** calling `SetPublicKey(key *rsa.PublicKey)`\n253: - **THEN** `a.mutex.Lock()` SHALL acquire write lock\n254: - AND `a.publicKey = key` SHALL update public key\n255: - AND `a.mutex.Unlock()` SHALL release lock\n256: \n257: #### Scenario: GetPublicKey thread-safe read\n258: - **GIVEN** `pkg/picod/auth.go`\n259: - **WHEN** calling `GetPublicKey()`\n260: - **THEN** `a.mutex.RLock()` SHALL acquire read lock\n261: - AND `defer a.mutex.RUnlock()` SHALL ensure release\n262: - AND `a.publicKey` SHALL be returned\n263: \n264: #### Scenario: Key rotation during active requests\n265: - **GIVEN** concurrent requests and SetPublicKey call\n266: - **WHEN** key rotation occurs\n267: - **THEN** existing request validation SHALL complete with old key (read lock held)\n268: - AND subsequent requests SHALL use new key\n269: - AND no request SHALL fail due to key rotation race\n270: \n271: #### Scenario: Router key rotation coordination\n272: - **GIVEN** Router generates new key pair\n273: - **WHEN** Workload Manager pushes new public key\n274: - **THEN** `SetPublicKey()` SHALL be called on AuthManager\n275: - AND PicoD SHALL validate new tokens with new public key\n276: - AND service restart SHALL NOT be required\n277: \n278: ---\n279: \n280: ### Requirement: Server integration\n281: \n282: The system SHALL integrate AuthManager into PicoD server with middleware registration.\n283: \n284: #### Scenario: Server AuthManager field\n285: - **GIVEN** `pkg/picod/server.go`\n286: - **WHEN** reading the `Server` struct\n287: - **THEN** `authManager *AuthManager` SHALL be present\n288: \n289: #### Scenario: NewServer AuthManager initialization\n290: - **GIVEN** `pkg/picod/server.go`\n291: - **WHEN** calling `NewServer(config)`\n292: - **THEN** `NewAuthManager()` SHALL be called\n293: - AND `authManager` SHALL be set in Server\n294: - AND error SHALL be returned if AuthManager creation fails\n295: \n296: #### Scenario: API route group middleware registration\n297: - **GIVEN** `pkg/picod/server.go`\n298: - **WHEN** registering `/api` route group\n299: - **THEN** `api.Use(s.authManager.AuthMiddleware())` SHALL apply middleware\n300: - AND all routes under `/api` SHALL require JWT authentication\n301: \n302: #### Scenario: Health endpoint authentication bypass\n303: - **GIVEN** `pkg/picod/server.go`\n304: - **WHEN** registering routes\n305: - **THEN** `/health` SHALL be registered directly on `engine` (not `/api` group)\n306: - AND `/health` SHALL NOT require JWT authentication\n307: - AND unauthenticated health check SHALL be available\n308: \n309: ---\n310: \n311: ### Requirement: Error handling\n312: \n313: The system SHALL handle JWT authentication errors with appropriate HTTP status codes and messages.\n314: \n315: #### Scenario: Missing Authorization header error\n316: - **GIVEN** request without Authorization header\n317: - **WHEN** AuthMiddleware rejects request\n318: - **THEN** HTTP `401` SHALL be returned\n319: - AND body SHALL be `{\"error\": \"missing authorization header\"}`\n320: \n321: #### Scenario: Invalid token format error\n322: - **GIVEN** Authorization header without Bearer prefix\n323: - **WHEN** AuthMiddleware rejects request\n324: - **THEN** HTTP `401` SHALL be returned\n325: - AND body SHALL be `{\"error\": \"invalid token format\"}`\n326: \n327: #### Scenario: Invalid signing method error\n328: - **GIVEN** JWT signed with non-RSA algorithm\n329: - **WHEN** AuthMiddleware rejects request\n330: - **THEN** HTTP `401` SHALL be returned\n331: - AND body SHALL be `{\"error\": \"invalid signing method\"}`\n332: \n333: #### Scenario: Expired token error\n334: - **GIVEN** JWT with expired exp claim\n335: - **WHEN** AuthMiddleware rejects request\n336: - **THEN** HTTP `401` SHALL be returned\n337: - AND body SHALL be `{\"error\": \"token is expired\"}`\n338: \n339: #### Scenario: Invalid signature error\n340: - **GIVEN** JWT with signature mismatch\n341: - **WHEN** AuthMiddleware rejects request\n342: - **THEN** HTTP `401` SHALL be returned\n343: - AND body SHALL be `{\"error\": \"invalid signature\"}`\n344: \n345: #### Scenario: Invalid token error\n346: - **GIVEN** JWT validation failure with token.Valid false\n347: - **WHEN** AuthMiddleware rejects request\n348: - **THEN** HTTP `401` SHALL be returned\n349: - AND body SHALL be `{\"error\": \"invalid token\"}`\n350: \n351: ---\n352: \n353: ### Requirement: Test coverage\n354: \n355: The system SHALL provide comprehensive test coverage for JWT middleware functionality.\n356: \n357: #### Scenario: Test missing authorization header\n358: - **GIVEN** `pkg/picod/picod_test.go`\n359: - **WHEN** testing AuthMiddleware without Authorization header\n360: - **THEN** HTTP `401` SHALL be returned\n361: - AND error message SHALL be `\"missing authorization header\"`\n362: \n363: #### Scenario: Test invalid token format\n364: - **GIVEN** `pkg/picod/picod_test.go`\n365: - **WHEN** testing AuthMiddleware with malformed Authorization header\n366: - **THEN** HTTP `401` SHALL be returned\n367: - AND error message SHALL be `\"invalid token format\"`\n368: \n369: #### Scenario: Test expired token\n370: - **GIVEN** `pkg/picod/picod_test.go`\n371: - **WHEN** testing AuthMiddleware with expired JWT\n372: - **THEN** HTTP `401` SHALL be returned\n373: - AND error message SHALL be `\"token is expired\"`\n374: \n375: #### Scenario: Test invalid signature\n376: - **GIVEN** `pkg/picod/picod_test.go`\n377: - **WHEN** testing AuthMiddleware with wrong signature\n378: - **THEN** HTTP `401` SHALL be returned\n379: - AND error message SHALL be `\"invalid signature\"`\n380: \n381: #### Scenario: Test HS256 rejection\n382: - **GIVEN** `pkg/picod/picod_test.go`\n383: - **WHEN** testing AuthMiddleware with HS256-signed JWT\n384: - **THEN** HTTP `401` SHALL be returned\n385: - AND error message SHALL be `\"invalid signing method\"`\n386: \n387: #### Scenario: Test valid RS256 token\n388: - **GIVEN** `pkg/picod/picod_test.go`\n389: - **WHEN** testing AuthMiddleware with valid RS256 JWT\n390: - **THEN** request SHALL proceed (c.Next called)\n391: - AND handler SHALL be invoked\n392: \n393: #### Scenario: Test key rotation\n394: - **GIVEN** `pkg/picod/picod_test.go`\n395: - **WHEN** testing SetPublicKey with new key\n396: - **THEN** subsequent requests SHALL validate with new key\n397: - AND old-key-signed tokens SHALL be rejected\n398: \n399: #### Scenario: Test PEM format validation\n400: - **GIVEN** `pkg/picod/picod_test.go`\n401: - **WHEN** testing LoadPublicKeyFromEnv with PKCS#1 PEM\n402: - **THEN** error SHALL be returned\n403: - AND error message SHALL indicate expected PUBLIC KEY block\n404: \n405: #### Scenario: Test environment variable missing\n406: - **GIVEN** `pkg/picod/picod_test.go`\n407: - **WHEN** testing LoadPublicKeyFromEnv with empty env var\n408: - **THEN** error SHALL be returned\n409: - AND error message SHALL indicate environment variable not set\n410: \n411: #### Scenario: Test concurrent key access\n412: - **GIVEN** `pkg/picod/picod_test.go`\n413: - **WHEN** testing concurrent SetPublicKey and GetPublicKey calls\n414: - **THEN** no race condition SHALL occur\n415: - AND mutex SHALL protect concurrent access\n416: \n417: ---\n418: \n419: ## Constants Summary\n420: \n421: | Constant | Value | File | Purpose |\n422: |----------|-------|------|---------|\n423: | `PublicKeyEnvVar` | `\"PICOD_AUTH_PUBLIC_KEY\"` | `auth.go` | Env var for PEM public key |\n424: | `MaxBodySize` | `32 << 20` | `auth.go` | Request body size limit (32 MiB) |\n425: \n426: ---\n427: \n428: ## Dependencies Summary\n429: \n430: | Package | Version | Purpose |\n431: |---------|---------|---------|\n432: | `github.com/gin-gonic/gin` | v1.10+ | Gin middleware pattern; `gin.HandlerFunc`, `gin.Context` |\n433: | `github.com/golang-jwt/jwt/v5` | v5.2+ | JWT parsing; RSA signing method validation, claim options |\n434: | `crypto/rsa` | Standard | RSA public key type |\n435: | `crypto/x509` | Standard | PKIX public key parsing |\n436: | `encoding/pem` | Standard | PEM block decoding |\n437: | `sync` | Standard | `sync.RWMutex` for thread-safe key storage |\n438: | `net/http` | Standard | `http.MaxBytesReader` for body limiting |\n439: \n440: ---\n441: \n442: ## File Changes Summary\n443: \n444: | File | Action | Description |\n445: |------|--------|-------------|\n446: | `pkg/picod/auth.go` | Document | `AuthManager`, `NewAuthManager`, `LoadPublicKeyFromEnv`, `AuthMiddleware`, `SetPublicKey`, `GetPublicKey` |\n447: | `pkg/picod/server.go` | Document | AuthManager integration, middleware registration |\n448: | `pkg/picod/picod_test.go` | Extend | Test coverage for JWT middleware, key rotation, PEM validation |\n449: \n450: ---\n451: \n452: ## References\n453: \n454: - `changes/AR-015/delta-spec.md` ŌĆö Original PicoD implementation\n455: - `pkg/router/jwt.go` ŌĆö Router JWT issuance (key pair generation)\n456: - [github.com/golang-jwt/jwt](https://github.com/golang-jwt/jwt)\n457: - [JWT Best Practices RFC 8725](https://datatracker.ietf.org/doc/html/rfc8725)\n\n(End of file - total 457 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# Delta Spec: AR-017 ŌĆö PicoD JWT õĖŁķŚ┤õ╗Č\n\n**Module:** `pkg/picod`  \n**Language:** Go  \n**Size:** S\n\n---\n\n## Overview\n\nImplement a dedicated JWT authentication middleware for PicoD that provides secure RS256 token validation, runtime public key management for key rotation, and request body size limiting. This middleware ensures that all PicoD API endpoints (except health check) require valid JWT tokens issued by the Router, protecting sandbox pods from unauthorized access.\n\n---\n\n## GIVEN/WHEN/THEN Scenarios\n\n### Requirement: AuthManager type definition\n\nThe system SHALL define `AuthManager` for RSA JWT authentication with thread-safe public key storage.\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-017/delta-spec.md","time":{"start":1775871197453,"end":1775871197469}}}}
