{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775871209062,"sessionID":"ses_285d45783ffe7V0U1N5fK5jOTG","part":{"id":"prt_d7a2c28ea001QSKvNQiMFUt8pP","messageID":"msg_d7a2c1825001p5lAqcQVXsnSXw","sessionID":"ses_285d45783ffe7V0U1N5fK5jOTG","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-0c9e1fb6528b4e97b2a1e5870f55aabd","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-022/delta-spec.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-022/delta-spec.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Delta Spec: AR-022 ŌĆö CLI publish ÕæĮõ╗ż\n2: \n3: **Module:** `cmd/cli`  \n4: **Language:** Python  \n5: **Size:** L\n6: \n7: ---\n8: \n9: ## Overview\n10: \n11: [TO BE FILLED: Overview of the publish command delta changes]\n12: \n13: ---\n14: \n15: ## GIVEN/WHEN/THEN Scenarios\n16: \n17: [TO BE FILLED: Define GIVEN/WHEN/THEN scenarios for each requirement]\n18: \n19: ---\n20: \n21: ## Constants Summary\n22: \n23: | Constant | Value | File | Purpose |\n24: |----------|-------|------|---------|\n25: | [TO BE FILLED] | [TO BE FILLED] | [TO BE FILLED] | [TO BE FILLED] |\n26: \n27: ---\n28: \n29: ## Dependencies Summary\n30: \n31: | Package | Version | Purpose |\n32: |---------|---------|---------|\n33: | [TO BE FILLED] | [TO BE FILLED] | [TO BE FILLED] |\n34: \n35: ---\n36: \n37: ## File Changes Summary\n38: \n39: | File | Action | Description |\n40: |------|--------|-------------|\n41: | [TO BE FILLED] | [TO BE FILLED] | [TO BE FILLED] |\n42: \n43: ---\n44: \n45: ## References\n46: \n47: - AR-021 ŌĆö CLI build command (prerequisite for built image)\n48: - AR-023 ŌĆö CLI invoke command\n49: - cli-toolkit/design.md ŌĆö CLI toolkit architecture\n50: - cli-toolkit/spec.md ŌĆö CLI specification\n51: \n52: ---\n53: \n54: ## Validation Checklist\n55: \n56: - [ ] [TO BE FILLED]\n\n(End of file - total 56 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# Delta Spec: AR-022 ŌĆö CLI publish ÕæĮõ╗ż\n\n**Module:** `cmd/cli`  \n**Language:** Python  \n**Size:** L\n\n---\n\n## Overview\n\n[TO BE FILLED: Overview of the publish command delta changes]\n\n---\n\n## GIVEN/WHEN/THEN Scenarios\n\n[TO BE FILLED: Define GIVEN/WHEN/THEN scenarios for each requirement]\n\n---\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-022/delta-spec.md","time":{"start":1775871209043,"end":1775871209060}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775871209065,"sessionID":"ses_285d45783ffe7V0U1N5fK5jOTG","part":{"id":"prt_d7a2c2b50001cC0OuK5l47UeKi","messageID":"msg_d7a2c1825001p5lAqcQVXsnSXw","sessionID":"ses_285d45783ffe7V0U1N5fK5jOTG","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-60d2c5821c664d7489bef8954de02e35","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-022/proposal.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-022/proposal.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-022 ŌĆö CLI publish ÕæĮõ╗ż\n2: \n3: ## µ”éĶ┐░\n4: \n5: | Õ▒×µĆ¦ | ÕĆ╝ |\n6: |------|-----|\n7: | AR | AR-022 |\n8: | Module | cmd/cli |\n9: | Language | Python |\n10: | Size | L |\n11: \n12: ---\n13: \n14: ## 1. Purpose (ńø«ńÜä)\n15: \n16: Implement the `publish` command in AgentCube CLI to deploy agent containers to Kubernetes. The command orchestrates the entire publish lifecycle: preparing container images (Docker push or explicit URL), deploying to target infrastructure (AgentCube AgentRuntime CR or standard Kubernetes Deployment/Service), and updating metadata with deployment information.\n17: \n18: **Current State**: CLI has `pack` and `build` commands that generate Dockerfile and build container images, but no deployment capability. Users must manually push images and create Kubernetes resources.\n19: \n20: **Target State**: \n21: - Single `kubectl-agentcube publish` command that deploys agents to Kubernetes\n22: - Support for two providers: `agentcube` (AgentRuntime CR) and `k8s` (Deployment + NodePort Service)\n23: - Automatic image preparation via Docker push or explicit image URL\n24: - Metadata updated with deployment info, agent_id, and endpoint URLs\n25: - Namespace, replicas, and NodePort configuration support\n26: \n27: ---\n28: \n29: ## 2. Scope (ĶīāÕø┤)\n30: \n31: ### 2.1 In Scope\n32: \n33: | Deliverable | Description |\n34: |-------------|-------------|\n35: | `agentcube/runtime/publish_runtime.py` | `PublishRuntime` class with publish orchestration logic |\n36: | `agentcube/cli/main.py` | `publish` Typer command with CLI options |\n37: | `agentcube/services/k8s_provider.py` | `KubernetesProvider` for standard K8s Deployment/Service |\n38: | `agentcube/services/agentcube_provider.py` | `AgentCubeProvider` for AgentRuntime CR deployment |\n39: | `agentcube/services/docker_service.py` | Image push methods (extends AR-021) |\n40: \n41: ### 2.2 PublishRuntime Methods\n42: \n43: | Method | Purpose |\n44: |--------|---------|\n45: | `publish(workspace_path, **options)` | Main orchestration entry point |\n46: | `_publish_cr_to_k8s(workspace_path, metadata, **options)` | Deploy via AgentCube AgentRuntime CR |\n47: | `_publish_k8s(workspace_path, metadata, **options)` | Deploy via standard Kubernetes Deployment/Service |\n48: | `_prepare_image_for_publishing(workspace_path, metadata, options)` | Image preparation (push or URL) |\n49: | `_prepare_local_image(workspace_path, metadata, options)` | Push local Docker image to registry |\n50: | `_prepare_cloud_image(workspace_path, metadata, options)` | Use cloud-built image URL |\n51: | `_update_publish_metadata(workspace_path, agent_info)` | Persist deployment info to metadata YAML |\n52: \n53: ### 2.3 CLI Options\n54: \n55: | Option | Type | Default | Description |\n56: |--------|------|---------|-------------|\n57: | `--workspace` / `-f` | `str` | `\".\"` | Path to agent workspace directory |\n58: | `--version` | `Optional[str]` | `None` | Semantic version string (e.g., v1.0.0) |\n59: | `--image-url` | `Optional[str]` | `None` | Image repository URL (required in local build mode) |\n60: | `--image-username` | `Optional[str]` | `None` | Username for image repository |\n61: | `--image-password` | `Optional[str]` | `None` | Password for image repository |\n62: | `--description` | `Optional[str]` | `None` | Agent description |\n63: | `--region` | `Optional[str]` | `None` | Deployment region |\n64: | `--cloud-provider` | `Optional[str]` | `None` | Cloud provider name (e.g., huawei) |\n65: | `--provider` | `str` | `\"agentcube\"` | Target provider: 'agentcube' or 'k8s' |\n66: | `--node-port` | `Optional[int]` | `None` | Specific NodePort (30000-32767) for K8s |\n67: | `--replicas` | `Optional[int]` | `None` | Number of replicas (default: 1) |\n68: | `--namespace` | `Optional[str]` | `None` | Kubernetes namespace |\n69: | `--verbose` | `bool` | `False` | Enable detailed logging |\n70: \n71: ### 2.4 Out of Scope\n72: \n73: | Item | Reason |\n74: |------|--------|\n75: | Cloud publish implementation | Requires cloud provider SDK integration; placeholder only |\n76: | Helm chart deployment | Different deployment paradigm; future enhancement |\n77: | Auto-scaling configuration | Not specified in requirements; HPA would be separate feature |\n78: | Secret management | Beyond current scope; requires vault integration |\n79: | Multi-cluster deployment | Requires federation setup; future enhancement |\n80: \n81: ---\n82: \n83: ## 3. Impact Analysis (ÕĮ▒ÕōŹÕłåµ×É)\n84: \n85: ### 3.1 µ¢░Õó×µ¢ćõ╗Č\n86: \n87: ```\n88: cmd/cli/\n89: Ōö£ŌöĆŌöĆ agentcube/\n90: Ōöé   Ōö£ŌöĆŌöĆ runtime/\n91: Ōöé   Ōöé   ŌööŌöĆŌöĆ publish_runtime.py     # PublishRuntime class\n92: Ōöé   Ōö£ŌöĆŌöĆ services/\n93: Ōöé   Ōöé   Ōö£ŌöĆŌöĆ k8s_provider.py        # KubernetesProvider class\n94: Ōöé   Ōöé   ŌööŌöĆŌöĆ agentcube_provider.py  # AgentCubeProvider class\n95: Ōöé   Ōöé   ŌööŌöĆŌöĆ docker_service.py      # (extend with push_image)\n96: Ōöé   ŌööŌöĆŌöĆ cli/\n97: Ōöé       ŌööŌöĆŌöĆ main.py                # publish command (addition to existing)\n98: ŌööŌöĆŌöĆ tests/\n99:     Ōö£ŌöĆŌöĆ test_publish_runtime.py    # Unit tests for PublishRuntime\n100:     Ōö£ŌöĆŌöĆ test_k8s_provider.py       # Unit tests for KubernetesProvider\n101:     ŌööŌöĆŌöĆ test_agentcube_provider.py # Unit tests for AgentCubeProvider\n102: ```\n103: \n104: ### 3.2 Upstream Dependencies\n105: \n106: | Dependency | Version | Impact |\n107: |------------|---------|--------|\n108: | `kubernetes` | `>=28.0.0` | Python client for Kubernetes API; optional dependency under `[k8s]` extras |\n109: | `docker` | `>=6.0.0` | Docker SDK for image push operations |\n110: | `pydantic` | `>=2.0.0` | Metadata model validation |\n111: | `rich` | `>=13.0.0` | Progress spinner and table output |\n112: | `pyyaml` | `>=6.0` | Metadata file read/write |\n113: | `httpx` | `>=0.24.0` | HTTP client for future cloud integration |\n114: \n115: ### 3.3 Downstream Consumers\n116: \n117: | Consumer | Method Usage |\n118: |----------|--------------|\n119: | `invoke` command | Uses agent_endpoint from metadata for HTTP calls |\n120: | `status` command | Reads k8s_deployment info from metadata |\n121: | `pack`/`build` commands | Provide image info for publish flow |\n122: | Users | CLI invocation `kubectl-agentcube publish -f ./my-agent` |\n123: \n124: ### 3.4 Breaking Change Considerations\n125: \n126: - **Metadata schema**: Adding `k8s_deployment` field with sub-fields (`type`, `deployment_name`, `service_name`, `namespace`, `replicas`, `node_port`, `service_url`, `agent_id`)\n127: - **Provider parameter**: New `--provider` flag changes behavior significantly\n128: - **AgentRuntime CR dependency**: Requires Volcano AgentCube CRD installed for `agentcube` provider\n129: - **Registry credentials**: Password passed via CLI flag (insecure); recommend env vars or secret files\n130: \n131: ### 3.5 Compatibility Notes\n132: \n133: - Kubernetes client `kubernetes.config.load_kube_config()` reads from `~/.kube/config` by default\n134: - NodePort range must be 30000-32767 per Kubernetes specification\n135: - AgentRuntime CR uses API group `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1`\n136: - Image URL format: `{registry}/{repository}/{image}:{tag}`\n137: \n138: ---\n139: \n140: ## 4. Alternatives Considered (ÕżćķĆēµ¢╣µĪł)\n141: \n142: ### Alternative 1: Direct kubectl Execution\n143: \n144: **Approach**: Generate YAML manifests and execute `kubectl apply` via `subprocess.run()`.\n145: \n146: | Aspect | Evaluation |\n147: |--------|------------|\n148: | Pros | Familiar to K8s users; no Python SDK dependency |\n149: | Cons | No programmatic status checks; harder error parsing; platform-specific; no wait-for-ready logic |\n150: \n151: **Decision**: Rejected. Kubernetes Python SDK provides typed API, wait loops, and structured status retrieval.\n152: \n153: ### Alternative 2: Helm Chart Publishing\n154: \n155: **Approach**: Package agent as Helm chart and use `helm install` for deployment.\n156: \n157: | Aspect | Evaluation |\n158: |--------|------------|\n159: | Pros | Standard K8s packaging; templating support; versioning built-in |\n160: | Cons | Requires Helm CLI; additional complexity; not in original spec |\n161: \n162: **Decision**: Rejected for initial scope. May add as alternative publishing mode in future.\n163: \n164: ### Alternative 3: Separate Push and Deploy Commands\n165: \n166: **Approach**: Split into `push-image` and `deploy` commands instead of unified `publish`.\n167: \n168: | Aspect | Evaluation |\n169: |--------|------------|\n170: | Pros | More granular control; can push without deploying |\n171: | Cons | More commands to learn; friction in typical workflow |\n172: \n173: **Decision**: Rejected. Unified `publish` command matches spec requirements and provides smoother user experience.\n174: \n175: ### Alternative 4: Docker Compose for Local Testing\n176: \n177: **Approach**: Support Docker Compose as deployment target for local development.\n178: \n179: | Aspect | Evaluation |\n180: |--------|------------|\n181: | Pros | Easy local testing; no K8s required |\n182: | Cons | Different networking model; not production-ready |\n183: \n184: **Decision**: Rejected. Focus on Kubernetes deployment per spec; local testing via `docker run` sufficient.\n185: \n186: ---\n187: \n188: ## 5. Risks\n189: \n190: | Risk | Mitigation |\n191: |------|------------|\n192: | Kubernetes cluster unreachable | Load kubeconfig first; fail early with clear error message |\n193: | AgentRuntime CRD not installed | `AgentCubeProvider` checks CR existence; raises `ValueError` if not found |\n194: | Missing router_url/workload_manager_url for agentcube | Validation in `_publish_cr_to_k8s` raises `ValueError` |\n195: | Image push auth failure | `DockerService._docker_login_sdk` handles credentials; log warning on failure |\n196: | Deployment timeout | `KubernetesProvider.wait_for_deployment_ready(timeout=120)` raises `TimeoutError` |\n197: | NodePort collision | K8s auto-assigns if NodePort not specified; validation for range 30000-32767 |\n198: \n199: ---\n200: \n201: ## 6. Implementation Checklist\n202: \n203: - [ ] Implement `KubernetesProvider.__init__()` with namespace, kubeconfig options\n204: - [ ] Implement `KubernetesProvider._ensure_namespace()` to create namespace if missing\n205: - [ ] Implement `KubernetesProvider.deploy_agent()` for Deployment + Service creation\n206: - [ ] Implement `KubernetesProvider._create_deployment()` with sanitization, env_vars\n207: - [ ] Implement `KubernetesProvider._create_service()` with NodePort handling\n208: - [ ] Implement `KubernetesProvider.wait_for_deployment_ready()` with timeout loop\n209: - [ ] Implement `KubernetesProvider.get_agent_status()` for pod/deployment status\n210: - [ ] Implement `KubernetesProvider.delete_agent()` for cleanup\n211: - [ ] Implement `KubernetesProvider._sanitize_name()` for K8s name compliance\n212: - [ ] Implement `AgentCubeProvider.__init__()` with namespace, kubeconfig options\n213: - [ ] Implement `AgentCubeProvider._ensure_namespace()` \n214: - [ ] Implement `AgentCubeProvider.deploy_agent_runtime()` for AgentRuntime CR\n215: - [ ] Implement `AgentCubeProvider._sanitize_name()` for CR name compliance\n216: - [ ] Implement `AgentCubeProvider.get_agent_runtime()` for CR status retrieval\n217: - [ ] Implement `PublishRuntime.publish()` orchestration entry point\n218: - [ ] Implement `PublishRuntime._publish_cr_to_k8s()` for AgentCube provider\n219: - [ ] Implement `PublishRuntime._publish_k8s()` for standard K8s provider\n220: - [ ] Implement `PublishRuntime._prepare_image_for_publishing()` image preparation\n221: - [ ] Implement `PublishRuntime._prepare_local_image()` Docker push logic\n222: - [ ] Implement `PublishRuntime._prepare_cloud_image()` cloud image URL handling\n223: - [ ] Implement `PublishRuntime._update_publish_metadata()` metadata persistence\n224: - [ ] Add `publish` Typer command in `agentcube/cli/main.py`\n225: - [ ] Add error handling with `_handle_error()` for verbose traceback\n226: - [ ] Add Rich `Progress` spinner for publish status\n227: - [ ] Add `k8s_deployment` and `agent_id` fields to `AgentMetadata` Pydantic model\n228: - [ ] Unit tests for KubernetesProvider mock K8s API\n229: - [ ] Unit tests for AgentCubeProvider mock CR API\n230: - [ ] Unit tests for image preparation logic\n231: - [ ] Integration test for full publish workflow (mocked)\n232: \n233: ---\n234: \n235: ## 7. References\n236: \n237: - Spec: `changes/AR-022/spec.md`\n238: - Design: `cli-toolkit/design.md`\n239: - CLI Spec: `cli-toolkit/spec.md` ŌĆö Requirement: `publish` command\n240: - Deployment Spec: `deployment/spec.md` ŌĆö Kubernetes deployment patterns\n241: - Python SDK Spec: `python-sdk/spec.md` ŌĆö AgentRuntimeClient integration\n242: - AR-021 ŌĆö CLI build command (image preparation dependency)\n243: - Kubernetes Python Client: https://github.com/kubernetes-client/python\n244: - Typer Documentation: https://typer.tiangolo.com/\n245: - Rich Library: https://rich.readthedocs.io/\n\n(End of file - total 245 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-022 ŌĆö CLI publish ÕæĮõ╗ż\n\n## µ”éĶ┐░\n\n| Õ▒×µĆ¦ | ÕĆ╝ |\n|------|-----|\n| AR | AR-022 |\n| Module | cmd/cli |\n| Language | Python |\n| Size | L |\n\n---\n\n## 1. Purpose (ńø«ńÜä)\n\nImplement the `publish` command in AgentCube CLI to deploy agent containers to Kubernetes. The command orchestrates the entire publish lifecycle: preparing container images (Docker push or explicit URL), deploying to target infrastructure (AgentCube AgentRuntime CR or standard Kubernetes Deployment/Service), and updating metadata with deployment information.\n\n**Current State**: CLI has `pack` and `build` commands that generate Dockerfile and build container images, but no deployment capability. Users must manually push images and create Kubernetes resources.\n\n**Target State**: ","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-022/proposal.md","time":{"start":1775871209046,"end":1775871209063}}}}
