{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775871344791,"sessionID":"ses_285d45783ffe7V0U1N5fK5jOTG","part":{"id":"prt_d7a2e4010001nVEBnwK5kNd1dK","messageID":"msg_d7a2c5b8800164zvC7k4ZrNg3C","sessionID":"ses_285d45783ffe7V0U1N5fK5jOTG","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_tool-299766f98ca549f5a2adf3b0ca3d9ba9","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-022/delta-spec.md","content":"# Delta Spec: AR-022 ŌĆö CLI publish ÕæĮõ╗ż\n\n**Module:** `cmd/cli`  \n**Language:** Python  \n**Size:** L\n\n---\n\n## Overview\n\nImplement the `publish` command in AgentCube CLI to deploy agent containers to Kubernetes. The command orchestrates the entire publish lifecycle: preparing container images (Docker push or explicit URL), deploying to target infrastructure (AgentCube AgentRuntime CR or standard Kubernetes Deployment/Service), and updating metadata with deployment information.\n\n---\n\n## GIVEN/WHEN/THEN Scenarios\n\n### Requirement: Publish Command Entry Point\n\nThe system SHALL provide a `publish` subcommand via Typer application to deploy agents to Kubernetes with provider selection.\n\n#### Scenario: Options and Defaults\n\n- **GIVEN** the user runs `publish` without specifying any options\n- **WHEN** the command is invoked\n- **THEN** the CLI SHALL use the following defaults:\n  - `workspace` = `\".\"` (`-f` / `--workspace`, type `str`)\n  - `version` = `None` (`--version`, type `Optional[str]`)\n  - `image_url` = `None` (`--image-url`, type `Optional[str]`)\n  - `image_username` = `None` (`--image-username`, type `Optional[str]`)\n  - `image_password` = `None` (`--image-password`, type `Optional[str]`)\n  - `description` = `None` (`--description`, type `Optional[str]`)\n  - `region` = `None` (`--region`, type `Optional[str]`)\n  - `cloud_provider` = `None` (`--cloud-provider`, type `Optional[str]`)\n  - `provider` = `\"agentcube\"` (`--provider`, type `str`)\n  - `node_port` = `None` (`--node-port`, type `Optional[int]`)\n  - `replicas` = `None` (`--replicas`, type `Optional[int]`)\n  - `namespace` = `None` (`--namespace`, type `Optional[str]`)\n  - `verbose` = `False` (`--verbose`, type `bool`)\n\n#### Scenario: Successful Publish with AgentCube Provider\n\n- **GIVEN** a valid workspace with metadata containing `agent_name`, `image`, `router_url`, and `workload_manager_url`\n- **WHEN** `publish` completes with `provider=\"agentcube\"`\n- **THEN** the CLI SHALL:\n  - Display a Rich Progress spinner during execution\n  - Print success message including `agent_id`, `agent_endpoint`, and deployment type\n  - Exit with code `0`\n\n#### Scenario: Successful Publish with Kubernetes Provider\n\n- **GIVEN** a valid workspace with metadata containing `agent_name`, `image`, and Kubernetes cluster accessible\n- **WHEN** `publish` completes with `provider=\"k8s\"`\n- **THEN** the CLI SHALL:\n  - Display a Rich Progress spinner during execution\n  - Print success message including `deployment_name`, `service_name`, `node_port`, and `service_url`\n  - Exit with code `0`\n\n#### Scenario: Publish Failure Handling with Verbose\n\n- **GIVEN** `PublishRuntime.publish` raises an exception\n- **WHEN** `verbose` is `True`\n- **THEN** the CLI SHALL:\n  - Print `Error publishing agent: {e}` in red via Rich\n  - Print the full traceback\n  - Exit with code `1`\n\n#### Scenario: Publish Failure Handling without Verbose\n\n- **GIVEN** `PublishRuntime.publish` raises an exception\n- **WHEN** `verbose` is `False`\n- **THEN** the CLI SHALL:\n  - Print `Error publishing agent: {e}` in red via Rich\n  - Exit with code `1` without printing traceback\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: PublishRuntime Initialization\n\nThe system SHALL construct `PublishRuntime` with provider selection.\n\n#### Scenario: PublishRuntime Constructor Default Provider\n\n- **GIVEN** `PublishRuntime(verbose=False)` is constructed\n- **WHEN** the instance is created\n- **THEN** the runtime SHALL:\n  - Set `provider` to `\"agentcube\"` (default)\n  - Initialize `MetadataService` for metadata operations\n  - Initialize `DockerService` for image push operations\n  - Store the `verbose` flag for logging control\n\n#### Scenario: PublishRuntime Constructor Explicit Provider\n\n- **GIVEN** `PublishRuntime(verbose=False, provider=\"k8s\")` is constructed\n- **WHEN** the instance is created\n- **THEN** the runtime SHALL:\n  - Set `provider` to `\"k8s\"`\n  - Initialize `KubernetesProvider` with default namespace `\"default\"`\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: PublishRuntime.publish Orchestration\n\nThe system SHALL orchestrate the publish workflow with validation, image preparation, deployment, and metadata update.\n\n#### Scenario: Load Metadata from Workspace\n\n- **GIVEN** a valid workspace path\n- **WHEN** `PublishRuntime.publish(workspace_path, **options)` runs\n- **THEN** the system SHALL:\n  - Call `MetadataService.load_metadata(workspace_path)`\n  - Validate metadata has required `agent_name` and `image` fields\n  - Raise `ValueError` if metadata is missing required fields\n\n#### Scenario: Apply CLI Option Overrides\n\n- **GIVEN** metadata loaded from workspace\n- **WHEN** CLI options are provided\n- **THEN** the system SHALL:\n  - Override `metadata.version` if `--version` is provided\n  - Override `metadata.description` if `--description` is provided\n  - Override `metadata.region` if `--region` is provided\n\n#### Scenario: Provider Selection Branching\n\n- **GIVEN** `provider` option is set\n- **WHEN** `PublishRuntime.publish` determines deployment method\n- **THEN** the system SHALL:\n  - Call `_publish_cr_to_k8s()` if `provider == \"agentcube\"`\n  - Call `_publish_k8s()` if `provider == \"k8s\"`\n  - Raise `ValueError` if `provider` is neither `\"agentcube\"` nor `\"k8s\"`\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: Image Preparation\n\nThe system SHALL prepare the container image for deployment via Docker push or explicit URL.\n\n#### Scenario: Prepare Image for Publishing\n\n- **GIVEN** metadata contains `build_mode`\n- **WHEN** `PublishRuntime._prepare_image_for_publishing()` runs\n- **THEN** the system SHALL:\n  - Call `_prepare_local_image()` if `build_mode == \"local\"`\n  - Call `_prepare_cloud_image()` if `build_mode == \"cloud\"`\n\n#### Scenario: Prepare Local Image with Registry\n\n- **GIVEN** `build_mode == \"local\"` and `image_url` is provided\n- **WHEN** `PublishRuntime._prepare_local_image()` runs\n- **THEN** the system SHALL:\n  - Call `DockerService.push_image()` with registry URL and credentials\n  - Return the pushed image URL `{registry_url}/{agent_name}:{version}`\n  - Raise `RuntimeError` if Docker push fails\n\n#### Scenario: Prepare Local Image Missing URL\n\n- **GIVEN** `build_mode == \"local\"` and `image_url` is not provided\n- **WHEN** `PublishRuntime._prepare_local_image()` runs\n- **THEN** the system SHALL raise `ValueError` indicating `--image-url` is required for local build mode\n\n#### Scenario: Prepare Cloud Image URL\n\n- **GIVEN** `build_mode == \"cloud\"` and `cloud_provider` is provided\n- **WHEN** `PublishRuntime._prepare_cloud_image()` runs\n- **THEN** the system SHALL:\n  - Return the image URL from `metadata.image` field\n  - Log warning if cloud publish is not fully implemented\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: AgentCube Provider Prerequisites\n\nThe system SHALL validate required fields before deploying via AgentCube provider.\n\n#### Scenario: Validate Router URL\n\n- **GIVEN** `provider == \"agentcube\"` and `metadata.router_url` is `None` or empty\n- **WHEN** `PublishRuntime._publish_cr_to_k8s()` runs\n- **THEN** the system SHALL raise `ValueError` with message requiring `router_url` in `agent_metadata.yaml`\n\n#### Scenario: Validate Workload Manager URL\n\n- **GIVEN** `provider == \"agentcube\"` and `metadata.workload_manager_url` is `None` or empty\n- **WHEN** `PublishRuntime._publish_cr_to_k8s()` runs\n- **THEN** the system SHALL raise `ValueError` with message requiring `workload_manager_url` in `agent_metadata.yaml`\n\n#### Scenario: Validate Readiness Probe Fields\n\n- **GIVEN** `provider == \"agentcube\"`\n- **WHEN** `AgentCubeProvider.deploy_agent_runtime()` runs\n- **THEN** the system SHALL use:\n  - `metadata.readiness_probe_path` or default `\"/health\"`\n  - `metadata.readiness_probe_port` or `metadata.port`\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: AgentCube Provider Deployment\n\nThe system SHALL deploy via AgentRuntime CR to Kubernetes.\n\n#### Scenario: AgentCubeProvider Initialization\n\n- **GIVEN** `AgentCubeProvider(namespace=\"default\", verbose=False)`\n- **WHEN** the provider is constructed\n- **THEN** the system SHALL:\n  - Load kubeconfig via `kubernetes.config.load_kube_config()`\n  - Initialize CustomObjectApi client for `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1`\n  - Set namespace to `\"default\"` or provided value\n\n#### Scenario: Ensure Namespace Exists\n\n- **GIVEN** `AgentCubeProvider` is initialized\n- **WHEN** `_ensure_namespace()` runs\n- **THEN** the system SHALL:\n  - Check if namespace exists via `CoreV1Api.read_namespace()`\n  - Create namespace if it does not exist\n  - Log creation in verbose mode\n\n#### Scenario: Deploy AgentRuntime CR\n\n- **GIVEN** `AgentCubeProvider.deploy_agent_runtime()` is called\n- **WHEN** the CR is created\n- **THEN** the system SHALL:\n  - Create CustomObject with `group=\"runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh\"`, `version=\"v1alpha1\"`, `plural=\"agentruntimes\"`\n  - Set CR name via `_sanitize_name(agent_name)` (lowercase, DNS compliant)\n  - Set `spec.image` to image URL\n  - Set `spec.port` to metadata port\n  - Set `spec.sessionTimeout` to `\"15m\"`\n  - Set `spec.maxSessionDuration` to `\"8h\"`\n  - Set `spec.imagePullSecrets` to `[{\"name\": \"default-secret\"}]`\n  - Embed `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL` and `ROUTER_URL` in `spec.env` when provided\n  - Return result dict with `agent_id`, `agent_endpoint`, `deployment_name`\n\n#### Scenario: Sanitize Name for CR\n\n- **GIVEN** `agent_name` contains special characters or uppercase\n- **WHEN** `AgentCubeProvider._sanitize_name(agent_name)` runs\n- **THEN** the system SHALL:\n  - Convert to lowercase\n  - Replace invalid characters with `-`\n  - Truncate to 63 characters if exceeds Kubernetes name limit\n\n#### Scenario: Patch Existing AgentRuntime CR\n\n- **GIVEN** an AgentRuntime CR with the same name already exists\n- **WHEN** `deploy_agent_runtime()` runs\n- **THEN** the system SHALL:\n  - Use `patch_custom_object` instead of `create_custom_object`\n  - Update image, port, and environment variables\n  - Return updated CR info\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: Kubernetes Provider Deployment\n\nThe system SHALL deploy via standard Kubernetes Deployment and NodePort Service.\n\n#### Scenario: KubernetesProvider Initialization\n\n- **GIVEN** `KubernetesProvider(namespace=\"default\", verbose=False)`\n- **WHEN** the provider is constructed\n- **THEN** the system SHALL:\n  - Load kubeconfig via `kubernetes.config.load_kube_config()`\n  - Initialize `AppsV1Api` for Deployment management\n  - Initialize `CoreV1Api` for Service and Namespace management\n  - Set namespace to `\"default\"` or provided value\n\n#### Scenario: Deploy Agent with Deployment and Service\n\n- **GIVEN** `KubernetesProvider.deploy_agent()` is called\n- **WHEN** deployment proceeds\n- **THEN** the system SHALL:\n  - Call `_create_deployment()` to create Deployment\n  - Call `_create_service()` to create NodePort Service\n  - Call `wait_for_deployment_ready()` with timeout `120`\n  - Return result dict with `deployment_name`, `service_name`, `namespace`, `replicas`, `container_port`, `node_port`, `service_url`\n\n#### Scenario: Create Deployment\n\n- **GIVEN** `KubernetesProvider._create_deployment()` is called\n- **WHEN** Deployment is created\n- **THEN** the system SHALL:\n  - Set Deployment name via `_sanitize_name(agent_name)`\n  - Set `spec.replicas` to provided value or `1`\n  - Set container image, port, and optional entrypoint command\n  - Add `env_vars` to container spec if provided\n  - Set `selector.matchLabels` and `template.metadata.labels` to `{\"app\": sanitized_name}`\n\n#### Scenario: Create NodePort Service\n\n- **GIVEN** `KubernetesProvider._create_service()` is called\n- **WHEN** Service is created\n- **THEN** the system SHALL:\n  - Set Service type to `NodePort`\n  - Set port to `metadata.port`\n  - Set `nodePort` to provided value if within range `30000-32767`\n  - Raise `ValueError` if `node_port` is outside valid range\n  - Allow Kubernetes to auto-assign NodePort if `node_port` is `None`\n\n#### Scenario: Wait for Deployment Ready\n\n- **GIVEN** deployment is created\n- **WHEN** `wait_for_deployment_ready(name, timeout=120)` runs\n- **THEN** the system SHALL:\n  - Poll deployment status every 2 seconds\n  - Check `status.availableReplicas == spec.replicas`\n  - Raise `TimeoutError` if timeout exceeded before ready\n  - Log progress in verbose mode\n\n#### Scenario: Deployment Readiness Failure\n\n- **GIVEN** deployment fails to become ready within timeout\n- **WHEN** `wait_for_deployment_ready()` exceeds timeout\n- **THEN** the system SHALL:\n  - Raise `RuntimeError` with deployment failure message\n  - Record error in metadata before raising\n\n#### Scenario: Delete Agent Resources\n\n- **GIVEN** `KubernetesProvider.delete_agent(agent_name)` is called\n- **WHEN** deletion proceeds\n- **THEN** the system SHALL:\n  - Delete Deployment via `delete_deployment()`\n  - Delete Service via `delete_service()`\n  - Ignore 404 errors for individual resources\n  - Return `{\"status\": \"deleted\", \"deployment_name\", \"namespace\"}`\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: Metadata Update After Publish\n\nThe system SHALL persist deployment information to metadata YAML.\n\n#### Scenario: Update Publish Metadata\n\n- **GIVEN** deployment completes successfully\n- **WHEN** `PublishRuntime._update_publish_metadata()` runs\n- **THEN** the system SHALL:\n  - Update `metadata.agent_id` from deployment result\n  - Update `metadata.agent_endpoint` from deployment result\n  - Update `metadata.k8s_deployment` with deployment info dict\n  - Save metadata via `MetadataService.save_metadata()`\n\n#### Scenario: k8s_deployment Field Structure\n\n- **GIVEN** metadata is updated after publish\n- **WHEN** `k8s_deployment` field is set\n- **THEN** the field SHALL contain:\n  - `type`: `\"AgentRuntime\"` for agentcube provider or `\"Deployment\"` for k8s provider\n  - `deployment_name`: sanitized deployment name\n  - `service_name`: sanitized service name (k8s provider)\n  - `namespace`: deployment namespace\n  - `replicas`: replica count\n  - `node_port`: NodePort number (k8s provider)\n  - `service_url`: `http://localhost:{node_port}` (k8s provider)\n\n#### Scenario: Record Error in Metadata on Failure\n\n- **GIVEN** deployment fails\n- **WHEN** error is recorded before raising\n- **THEN** the system SHALL:\n  - Set `k8s_deployment.error` to error message\n  - Set `k8s_deployment.status` to `\"error\"`\n  - Save metadata before raising exception\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: Namespace Configuration\n\nThe system SHALL support namespace configuration via CLI option.\n\n#### Scenario: Use Specified Namespace\n\n- **GIVEN** `--namespace my-namespace` is provided\n- **WHEN** provider is initialized\n- **THEN** the system SHALL:\n  - Pass namespace to `KubernetesProvider` or `AgentCubeProvider`\n  - Create resources in specified namespace\n\n#### Scenario: Default Namespace\n\n- **GIVEN** `--namespace` is not provided\n- **WHEN** provider is initialized\n- **THEN** the system SHALL:\n  - Use namespace from `metadata.k8s_deployment.namespace` if exists\n  - Use `\"default\"` as fallback\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: Replicas Configuration\n\nThe system SHALL support replica count configuration.\n\n#### Scenario: Use Specified Replicas\n\n- **GIVEN** `--replicas 3` is provided\n- **WHEN** Kubernetes Deployment is created\n- **THEN** `spec.replicas` SHALL be set to `3`\n\n#### Scenario: Default Replicas\n\n- **GIVEN** `--replicas` is not provided\n- **WHEN** Kubernetes Deployment is created\n- **THEN** `spec.replicas` SHALL default to `1`\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: NodePort Configuration\n\nThe system SHALL support NodePort specification for Kubernetes Service.\n\n#### Scenario: Use Specified NodePort\n\n- **GIVEN** `--node-port 30080` is provided\n- **WHEN** Kubernetes Service is created\n- **THEN** `spec.ports[0].nodePort` SHALL be set to `30080`\n\n#### Scenario: NodePort Range Validation\n\n- **GIVEN** `--node-port 20000` is provided (outside range)\n- **WHEN** `_create_service()` validates\n- **THEN** the system SHALL raise `ValueError` indicating NodePort must be in range `30000-32767`\n\n#### Scenario: Auto-assign NodePort\n\n- **GIVEN** `--node-port` is not provided\n- **WHEN** Kubernetes Service is created\n- **THEN** Kubernetes SHALL auto-assign a NodePort within valid range\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: Version Override\n\nThe system SHALL support version string override.\n\n#### Scenario: Override Version via CLI\n\n- **GIVEN** `--version v1.0.0` is provided\n- **WHEN** metadata is updated before publish\n- **THEN** `metadata.version` SHALL be set to `\"v1.0.0\"`\n\n#### Scenario: Use Metadata Version\n\n- **GIVEN** `--version` is not provided and metadata has `version`\n- **WHEN** image is tagged or pushed\n- **THEN** the system SHALL use existing `metadata.version`\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: Registry Credentials\n\nThe system SHALL support registry authentication for image push.\n\n#### Scenario: Push Image with Credentials\n\n- **GIVEN** `--image-username` and `--image-password` are provided\n- **WHEN** `DockerService.push_image()` runs\n- **THEN** the system SHALL:\n  - Call `_docker_login_sdk()` with credentials\n  - Login to registry before push\n  - Stream push logs in verbose mode\n\n#### Scenario: Push Image without Credentials\n\n- **GIVEN** `--image-username` and `--image-password` are not provided\n- **WHEN** `DockerService.push_image()` runs\n- **THEN** the system SHALL:\n  - Skip login step\n  - Attempt push assuming pre-authenticated Docker client\n  - Log warning if push fails due to auth\n\n#### Scenario: Docker Login SDK Method\n\n- **GIVEN** `DockerService._docker_login_sdk(registry, username, password)` is called\n- **WHEN** login executes\n- **THEN** the system SHALL:\n  - Use `docker.from_env().login()` method\n  - Handle login failure gracefully\n  - Log success/failure message\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: Image Tag and Retag\n\nThe system SHALL handle image tagging and retagging for registry push.\n\n#### Scenario: Tag Image for Registry\n\n- **GIVEN** local image `{agent_name}:latest`\n- **WHEN** `_prepare_local_image()` prepares for push\n- **THEN** the system SHALL:\n  - Tag image as `{registry_url}/{agent_name}:{version}`\n  - Call `_tag_image_sdk()` for Docker SDK tagging\n\n#### Scenario: Tag Image SDK Method\n\n- **GIVEN** `DockerService._tag_image_sdk(source_image, target_image)` is called\n- **WHEN** tagging executes\n- **THEN** `docker_client.images.get(source_image).tag(target_image)` SHALL be called\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: Error Handling Patterns\n\nThe system SHALL handle errors with appropriate messages and metadata updates.\n\n#### Scenario: Kubernetes Cluster Unreachable\n\n- **GIVEN** kubeconfig cannot connect to cluster\n- **WHEN** provider initialization runs\n- **THEN** the system SHALL raise `RuntimeError` with message indicating cluster unreachable\n\n#### Scenario: AgentRuntime CRD Not Installed\n\n- **GIVEN** `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1` CRD does not exist\n- **WHEN** `AgentCubeProvider.deploy_agent_runtime()` attempts CR creation\n- **THEN** the system SHALL:\n  - Catch API exception for CRD not found\n  - Raise `ValueError` indicating AgentCube CRD must be installed\n\n#### Scenario: Image Push Auth Failure\n\n- **GIVEN** registry credentials are invalid\n- **WHEN** `DockerService.push_image()` attempts push\n- **THEN** the system SHALL:\n  - Catch Docker API exception\n  - Raise `RuntimeError` with auth failure message\n  - Log detailed error in verbose mode\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: Verbose Logging\n\nThe system SHALL enable detailed logging when `--verbose` is passed.\n\n#### Scenario: Verbose Logging During Publish\n\n- **GIVEN** `--verbose` is passed to publish command\n- **WHEN** publish runs\n- **THEN** `PublishRuntime` SHALL:\n  - Log each step: metadata loading, image preparation, deployment\n  - Log Kubernetes API calls and responses\n  - Log Docker push progress\n  - Include intermediate results in logs\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: Progress Indicator During Publish\n\nThe system SHALL display a progress spinner during publish operations.\n\n#### Scenario: Rich Progress Spinner Display\n\n- **GIVEN** the publish command is executing\n- **WHEN** operations like image push and deployment run\n- **THEN** the CLI SHALL display a Rich Progress spinner with descriptive text (e.g., \"Publishing agent to Kubernetes...\")\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: Publish Result Structure\n\nThe system SHALL return a structured result from `PublishRuntime.publish`.\n\n#### Scenario: Return Publish Result Dictionary\n\n- **GIVEN** `PublishRuntime.publish` completes successfully\n- **WHEN** the method returns\n- **THEN** the result SHALL be a `Dict[str, Any]` containing:\n  - `agent_name`: the resolved agent name\n  - `agent_id`: assigned agent ID (agentcube provider)\n  - `agent_endpoint`: endpoint URL for invoking agent\n  - `deployment_type`: `\"AgentRuntime\"` or `\"Deployment\"`\n  - `namespace`: deployment namespace\n  - `k8s_deployment`: full deployment info dict\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: Provider Selection Validation\n\nThe system SHALL validate provider selection.\n\n#### Scenario: Valid Provider Values\n\n- **GIVEN** `--provider agentcube` or `--provider k8s` is provided\n- **WHEN** provider is validated\n- **THEN** the system SHALL accept the value and proceed\n\n#### Scenario: Invalid Provider Value\n\n- **GIVEN** `--provider helm` is provided\n- **WHEN** provider is validated\n- **THEN** the system SHALL raise `ValueError` indicating valid providers are `agentcube` and `k8s`\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: Publish Command Help Text\n\nThe system SHALL provide help text for all publish command options.\n\n#### Scenario: Publish Command Help Display\n\n- **GIVEN** the user runs `publish --help`\n- **WHEN** the help is displayed\n- **THEN** Typer SHALL show:\n  - Command description\n  - All options with their names, types, defaults, and help strings\n  - Usage examples if configured\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: Workspace Path Resolution\n\nThe system SHALL resolve the workspace path to an absolute path.\n\n#### Scenario: Resolve Relative Workspace Path\n\n- **GIVEN** `workspace = \".\"` (relative path)\n- **WHEN** the publish command processes the workspace\n- **THEN** the system SHALL resolve it to an absolute path using `Path(workspace).resolve()`\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: Kubernetes Python SDK Integration\n\nThe system SHALL use kubernetes Python client for API interactions.\n\n#### Scenario: Load Kubeconfig\n\n- **GIVEN** `kubeconfig` is not specified\n- **WHEN** provider initializes\n- **THEN** `kubernetes.config.load_kube_config()` SHALL be called to load from `~/.kube/config`\n\n#### Scenario: Load Explicit Kubeconfig\n\n- **GIVEN** `kubeconfig` path is specified\n- **WHEN** provider initializes\n- **THEN** `kubernetes.config.load_kube_config(config_file=kubeconfig)` SHALL be called\n\n---\n\n## Constants Summary\n\n| Constant | Value | File | Purpose |\n|----------|-------|------|---------|\n| Default namespace | `\"default\"` | `k8s_provider.py`, `agentcube_provider.py` | Fallback namespace for deployments |\n| Default replicas | `1` | `k8s_provider.py` | Default replica count for Deployment |\n| Deployment timeout | `120` | `k8s_provider.py` | Seconds to wait for deployment readiness |\n| Poll interval | `2` | `k8s_provider.py` | Seconds between readiness checks |\n| NodePort min | `30000` | `k8s_provider.py` | Minimum valid NodePort |\n| NodePort max | `32767` | `k8s_provider.py` | Maximum valid NodePort |\n| Session timeout | `\"15m\"` | `agentcube_provider.py` | AgentRuntime session timeout |\n| Max session duration | `\"8h\"` | `agentcube_provider.py` | AgentRuntime max session duration |\n| ImagePullSecret | `\"default-secret\"` | `agentcube_provider.py` | Default image pull secret name |\n| CR API group | `\"runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh\"` | `agentcube_provider.py` | AgentRuntime CR API group |\n| CR API version | `\"v1alpha1\"` | `agentcube_provider.py` | AgentRuntime CR API version |\n| CR plural | `\"agentruntimes\"` | `agentcube_provider.py` | AgentRuntime CR plural name |\n\n---\n\n## Dependencies Summary\n\n| Package | Version | Purpose |\n|---------|---------|---------|\n| `typer[all]` | `>=0.9.0` | CLI framework with Rich integration |\n| `pydantic` | `>=2.0.0` | Metadata model validation |\n| `pyyaml` | `>=6.0` | Metadata file read/write |\n| `docker` | `>=6.0.0` | Docker SDK for image push operations |\n| `kubernetes` | `>=28.0.0` | Kubernetes Python client for Deployment/Service/CR management (optional `[k8s]` dependency) |\n| `rich` | `>=13.0.0` | Progress spinner and error display |\n| `httpx` | `>=0.24.0` | HTTP client for future cloud integration |\n| `pathlib` | (stdlib) | Path resolution |\n\n---\n\n## File Changes Summary\n\n| File | Action | Description |\n|------|--------|-------------|\n| `agentcube/cli/main.py` | Extend | Add `publish` Typer command with all CLI options |\n| `agentcube/runtime/publish_runtime.py` | Create | `PublishRuntime` class with publish orchestration |\n| `agentcube/services/k8s_provider.py` | Create | `KubernetesProvider` for Deployment/Service management |\n| `agentcube/services/agentcube_provider.py` | Create | `AgentCubeProvider` for AgentRuntime CR deployment |\n| `agentcube/services/docker_service.py` | Extend | Add `push_image`, `_docker_login_sdk`, `_tag_image_sdk` methods |\n| `agentcube/services/metadata_service.py` | Extend | Handle `k8s_deployment` and `agent_id` fields |\n| `tests/test_publish_runtime.py` | Create | Unit tests for PublishRuntime |\n| `tests/test_k8s_provider.py` | Create | Unit tests for KubernetesProvider |\n| `tests/test_agentcube_provider.py` | Create | Unit tests for AgentCubeProvider |\n\n---\n\n## References\n\n- AR-021 ŌĆö CLI build command (prerequisite for built image)\n- AR-023 ŌĆö CLI invoke command\n- AR-024 ŌĆö CLI status command\n- cli-toolkit/design.md ŌĆö CLI toolkit architecture\n- cli-toolkit/spec.md ŌĆö CLI specification\n- deployment/spec.md ŌĆö Kubernetes deployment patterns\n- Kubernetes Python Client: https://github.com/kubernetes-client/python\n- Typer Documentation: https://typer.tiangolo.com/\n- Rich Library: https://rich.readthedocs.io/\n\n---\n\n## Validation Checklist\n\n- [ ] Publish command registered in Typer app with correct options\n- [ ] Options have correct types and defaults matching spec\n- [ ] PublishRuntime orchestrates validation, image prep, deployment, metadata update\n- [ ] AgentCube provider validates router_url and workload_manager_url\n- [ ] Kubernetes provider creates Deployment and NodePort Service\n- [ ] NodePort range validation (30000-32767) implemented\n- [ ] wait_for_deployment_ready with 120s timeout implemented\n- [ ] AgentRuntime CR created with correct API group/version/plural\n- [ ] CR includes sessionTimeout=\"15m\", maxSessionDuration=\"8h\"\n- [ ] Image push with Docker SDK and registry credentials\n- [ ] Metadata updated with agent_id, agent_endpoint, k8s_deployment\n- [ ] Error handling updates metadata before raising\n- [ ] Verbose mode enables detailed logging\n- [ ] Rich Progress spinner displayed during execution\n- [ ] Provider selection validation (agentcube/k8s)\n- [ ] Namespace support from CLI option or metadata\n- [ ] Replicas and NodePort configuration supported\n- [ ] Version override via CLI option\n- [ ] Unit tests for all components with mocked K8s/Docker APIs"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{},"filepath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-022/delta-spec.md","exists":true,"truncated":false},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-022/delta-spec.md","time":{"start":1775871344746,"end":1775871344786}}}}
